1
00:00:04,440 --> 00:00:07,780
(Outdoor survival grounds)

2
00:00:08,240 --> 00:00:09,940
Gosh, it's so cold.

3
00:00:10,480 --> 00:00:13,210
- We can't even sit.
- Let's sit on the floor.

4
00:00:13,580 --> 00:00:16,120
Should we do some push-ups
since it's so cold?

5
00:00:17,820 --> 00:00:19,220
I don't want to do anything right now.

6
00:00:19,590 --> 00:00:21,160
I feel like I should warm up.

7
00:00:21,820 --> 00:00:22,960
I'm very sensitive to cold,

8
00:00:22,960 --> 00:00:24,830
and it was raining and freezing.

9
00:00:25,090 --> 00:00:26,560
I was shivering.

10
00:00:26,860 --> 00:00:28,260
I hate bugs so much,

11
00:00:28,460 --> 00:00:32,470
but I realized today
that the cold was scarier than bugs.

12
00:00:33,100 --> 00:00:34,570
It's freezing.

13
00:00:37,340 --> 00:00:39,170
It's too cold.

14
00:00:42,380 --> 00:00:45,080
If it wasn't raining,
I would have gone outside...

15
00:00:45,080 --> 00:00:47,250
to gather wood
and found a way to make a fire.

16
00:00:50,590 --> 00:00:52,820
Should we check out what's upstairs?

17
00:00:53,290 --> 00:00:55,360
- Yes.
- It's cold, anyway.

18
00:00:56,160 --> 00:00:57,730
- Let's check it out.
- Okay.

19
00:00:58,160 --> 00:00:59,230
So cold.

20
00:01:00,630 --> 00:01:02,600
(Groaning)

21
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:05,200
(Groaning)

22
00:01:05,200 --> 00:01:06,370
(Sighing)

23
00:01:07,170 --> 00:01:08,770
(Exclaiming)

24
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:11,970
(They can't help but groan
in this cold weather.)

25
00:01:14,910 --> 00:01:16,580
I hope we find something.

26
00:01:17,550 --> 00:01:18,950
Anything that's warm.

27
00:01:23,180 --> 00:01:26,220
- It's cold.
- There are things here.

28
00:01:29,720 --> 00:01:31,790
When you go to a theme park,

29
00:01:31,790 --> 00:01:33,530
- there's a haunted house.
- Exactly.

30
00:01:42,240 --> 00:01:43,470
It says, "Ghost Casino."

31
00:01:43,470 --> 00:01:45,210
- Is it already open?
- It's here.

32
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:46,840
- There's something here.
- No way.

33
00:01:47,080 --> 00:01:49,980
- I guess we're supposed to use garlic.
- Yes.

34
00:01:51,780 --> 00:01:53,010
Oh, like this.

35
00:01:55,180 --> 00:01:56,920
There it is. There's fire steel.

36
00:01:57,720 --> 00:01:59,120
- Then...
- And there's beer!

37
00:01:59,550 --> 00:02:00,620
That sounds good.

38
00:02:02,860 --> 00:02:04,590
You get 1 coin for 100g.

39
00:02:04,930 --> 00:02:07,400
It's 1 coin for 3kg of garlic?
What does this mean?

40
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:11,570
If a fire steel is 2 coins,
we have to peel 6kg of garlic.

41
00:02:12,400 --> 00:02:13,970
And we need firewood.

42
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:17,470
We'd need a mortal set first.

43
00:02:17,670 --> 00:02:21,080
If we crush the garlic, we get more coins.

44
00:02:21,940 --> 00:02:24,450
So, we'll spend the entire time...

45
00:02:24,450 --> 00:02:27,580
peeling garlic until Ghost Casino opens.

46
00:02:27,680 --> 00:02:28,980
- Yes.
- And we can play games...

47
00:02:28,980 --> 00:02:31,750
- And we make more coins.
- to win double the coins.

48
00:02:32,220 --> 00:02:33,650
That seems like the only way.

49
00:02:33,990 --> 00:02:35,820
Let's just go and peel some garlic.

50
00:02:35,820 --> 00:02:38,030
Let's get going.

51
00:02:38,990 --> 00:02:40,960
Should we bring something to sit on?

52
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:42,760
Like a stool?

53
00:02:46,270 --> 00:02:48,170
Is there anything we can take?

54
00:02:54,540 --> 00:02:55,580
Here.

55
00:02:55,740 --> 00:02:56,910
That looks all right.

56
00:02:56,910 --> 00:02:58,910
(Yeon Cheong sighing)

57
00:02:59,150 --> 00:03:00,580
I would never have cared.

58
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:02,520
It was dirtier than a carpet.

59
00:03:02,520 --> 00:03:04,520
(Sighing)

60
00:03:10,260 --> 00:03:13,430
I got all the fabric I found
on the second floor.

61
00:03:13,590 --> 00:03:17,370
Although it was a bad environment,
I was sure we could find...

62
00:03:17,370 --> 00:03:19,000
something that was helpful.

63
00:03:20,770 --> 00:03:23,840
(They created a living space.)

64
00:03:27,070 --> 00:03:28,410
Let's hurry up.

65
00:03:31,510 --> 00:03:32,550
I'm hungry.

66
00:03:33,410 --> 00:03:34,480
Oh, no.

67
00:03:35,920 --> 00:03:39,120
Will the ones out there get
delicious food today?

68
00:03:39,390 --> 00:03:40,790
- They'll probably have a barbecue.
- They won't have to worry about food.

69
00:03:40,790 --> 00:03:41,920
They'll probably have a barbecue.

70
00:03:41,920 --> 00:03:44,290
I bet they already took a shower.

71
00:03:44,290 --> 00:03:46,890
I'm so jealous.
I wish I could wash my face.

72
00:03:47,930 --> 00:03:50,100
Your mom worked so hard...

73
00:03:50,360 --> 00:03:52,970
to send you to SNU, and you're here.

74
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:56,240
Do you know any methods
to peel garlic faster?

75
00:03:56,940 --> 00:03:58,110
Should we try using our teeth?

76
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:02,740
I'm worried that
we'll deal with garlic all day...

77
00:04:03,010 --> 00:04:04,880
and they'll look down on us.

78
00:04:05,210 --> 00:04:07,080
- Because of the smell?
- Because of the smell.

79
00:04:09,480 --> 00:04:11,590
That would be so humiliating.

80
00:04:14,220 --> 00:04:15,290
It's raining harder.

81
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:19,390
I think the sun is going down.

82
00:04:19,390 --> 00:04:20,900
It'll get way colder, then.

83
00:04:21,460 --> 00:04:22,500
We're in trouble.

84
00:04:24,270 --> 00:04:25,630
Should one of us crush them now?

85
00:04:25,930 --> 00:04:27,240
- I'll do that.
- Okay.

86
00:04:31,240 --> 00:04:33,310
(The garlic cloves pop out.)

87
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:34,480
Our precious garlic.

88
00:04:35,410 --> 00:04:36,780
That smell of garlic is...

89
00:04:40,350 --> 00:04:43,820
No wonder it's worth three times more.
It takes a lot of work.

90
00:04:44,190 --> 00:04:46,020
It won't be so easy
to crush 1kg of garlic.

91
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:47,120
Definitely not.

92
00:04:47,760 --> 00:04:48,790
Darn it.

93
00:04:48,990 --> 00:04:50,730
I shouldn't swear after having a baby.

94
00:04:50,730 --> 00:04:52,730
(The bell rings.)

95
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:55,000
- There's something in the mailbox.
- The mailbox?

96
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:56,760
(The mailbox is in a corner
of the outdoor survival grounds.)

97
00:04:59,030 --> 00:05:01,340
"Ghost Casino is open." Yes.

98
00:05:01,340 --> 00:05:02,440
Let's go. Take everything.

99
00:05:03,570 --> 00:05:04,640
Oh, my back.

100
00:05:07,240 --> 00:05:08,310
Let's give it a go.

101
00:05:11,750 --> 00:05:13,280
Let's do a chant before we go.

102
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:16,850
Our sleep depends on this.

103
00:05:17,490 --> 00:05:18,920
- What should we chant?
- I'm serious.

104
00:05:19,690 --> 00:05:21,820
"Rookie, Rookie, Rookie, yes!"

105
00:05:21,820 --> 00:05:22,960
- Okay.
- Start.

106
00:05:23,060 --> 00:05:24,730
- Rookie, Rookie, Rookie, yes!
- Rookie, Rookie, Rookie, yes!

107
00:05:25,090 --> 00:05:26,560
You can't go up by yourself.

108
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:27,860
It's weird to go down.

109
00:05:27,860 --> 00:05:29,600
- Let's go up. Start.
- Up.

110
00:05:29,660 --> 00:05:31,170
- Rookie, Rookie, Rookie, yes!
- Rookie, Rookie, Rookie, yes!

111
00:05:31,170 --> 00:05:32,900
- Let's go.
- That was motivating.

112
00:05:34,100 --> 00:05:35,770
Even if...

113
00:05:35,870 --> 00:05:38,840
we don't win anything,
let's not get mad at each other.

114
00:05:39,010 --> 00:05:40,740
- Don't blame each other.
- Don't blame each other.

115
00:05:40,740 --> 00:05:43,380
- Let's not blame anyone.
- Don't blame anyone.

116
00:05:43,440 --> 00:05:45,110
I feel like you'll be the angriest.

117
00:05:45,110 --> 00:05:47,350
No, I rarely get angry.

118
00:05:47,350 --> 00:05:48,450
- Really?
- Yes.

119
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:52,350
But I'm sure I'll get angry
at least once during this show.

120
00:05:53,150 --> 00:05:55,320
It's pretty heavy, including the potatoes.

121
00:05:55,320 --> 00:05:57,220
I know, right?
It must weigh like 4 or 5kg.

122
00:05:57,220 --> 00:05:58,830
- Yes, about 4 to 5kg.
- Seriously?

123
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:03,500
- What?
- What?

124
00:06:03,860 --> 00:06:05,230
Wait, there's a ghost.

125
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:07,700
There's a ghost.

126
00:06:18,010 --> 00:06:20,380
(Ghost Casino)

127
00:06:21,820 --> 00:06:25,120
Good evening, everyone.
Welcome to Ghost Casino.

128
00:06:25,250 --> 00:06:29,260
At Ghost Casino, you can trade
your ingredients in and earn coins.

129
00:06:29,560 --> 00:06:31,390
- Should we start with the potatoes?
- Yes.

130
00:06:31,390 --> 00:06:32,560
Let's put one up.

131
00:06:33,490 --> 00:06:35,430
Please remove the aluminum foil.

132
00:06:36,160 --> 00:06:37,430
We were going to.

133
00:06:38,230 --> 00:06:39,270
That's harsh.

134
00:06:41,100 --> 00:06:42,140
That's harsh.

135
00:06:44,540 --> 00:06:45,710
(Sniffling)

136
00:06:48,680 --> 00:06:51,610
- I should have rubbed some dirt on it.
- I know. We should have.

137
00:06:51,610 --> 00:06:53,110
Why didn't I think of that?

138
00:06:53,380 --> 00:06:55,050
- I think it's 1kg.
- Is it heavy?

139
00:06:55,050 --> 00:06:56,550
That's 900g. We get 9 coins.

140
00:06:56,550 --> 00:06:58,050
- It's 900g.
- Yes, 9 coins.

141
00:06:58,050 --> 00:06:59,490
- Yes.
- We'll trade them in.

142
00:06:59,650 --> 00:07:03,190
The ingredients weigh 900g,
so you will get 9 coins.

143
00:07:03,190 --> 00:07:04,190
Will you trade them in?

144
00:07:04,190 --> 00:07:05,260
- Yes.
- Yes!

145
00:07:05,830 --> 00:07:08,530
Here are nine coins based on the weight.

146
00:07:08,630 --> 00:07:10,870
Then, how long is your shop open?

147
00:07:11,130 --> 00:07:13,130
Ghost Casino will stay open,

148
00:07:13,130 --> 00:07:14,540
so you can always return.

149
00:07:14,540 --> 00:07:15,670
Really?

150
00:07:15,970 --> 00:07:18,610
Should we get these and stay warm?

151
00:07:18,610 --> 00:07:21,580
But we need money to bet.

152
00:07:21,580 --> 00:07:23,440
But we could lose.

153
00:07:23,540 --> 00:07:26,680
- We have to buy these, after all.
- If we save these four coins...

154
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:28,450
- and play games...
- To win more coins?

155
00:07:28,450 --> 00:07:30,020
Yes, if we win more...

156
00:07:30,020 --> 00:07:33,090
- What would you get with that?
- If you bet more coins,

157
00:07:33,090 --> 00:07:34,620
- you win more coins.
- Yes.

158
00:07:34,860 --> 00:07:37,830
We win 4 coins if we bet 2,
but we win 8 if we bet 4.

159
00:07:38,130 --> 00:07:41,300
Trust me. I think we should save them
and bet them later.

160
00:07:41,530 --> 00:07:43,600
I'll buy the mortar set
and crush the garlic.

161
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:46,030
- Mortar?
- Let's buy that and make more coins.

162
00:07:46,370 --> 00:07:48,300
- We're out of options.
- The mortar set.

163
00:07:48,500 --> 00:07:52,010
The items you bought will be brought
to the survival grounds.

164
00:07:52,410 --> 00:07:53,410
You even deliver them?

165
00:07:55,410 --> 00:07:57,480
Please make it express delivery.
We're in a hurry.

166
00:07:58,450 --> 00:07:59,710
Yes, thank you.

167
00:08:01,220 --> 00:08:03,220
We'll save as many as we can
to bet more coins.

168
00:08:03,820 --> 00:08:06,050
- And buy beer.
- Sounds good.

169
00:08:06,820 --> 00:08:08,060
We can do this, Beom.

170
00:08:08,390 --> 00:08:09,860
- Hang in there.
- We will.

171
00:08:12,530 --> 00:08:14,230
I was too weak just now.

172
00:08:15,360 --> 00:08:18,000
It was so cold
that I wanted to buy firewood first.

173
00:08:18,770 --> 00:08:20,870
We can't be so soft on the first day.

174
00:08:20,870 --> 00:08:22,440
What's our dream? To win the show.

175
00:08:22,570 --> 00:08:23,640
I like that.

176
00:08:24,510 --> 00:08:25,710
It's here.

177
00:08:26,140 --> 00:08:29,510
(The mortar set arrives.)

178
00:08:36,950 --> 00:08:38,350
But it's too small.

179
00:08:38,350 --> 00:08:39,990
When are we going to crush all the garlic?

180
00:08:39,990 --> 00:08:42,760
- We'll put a little bit in.
- Let me do it.

181
00:08:43,760 --> 00:08:46,830
We can only put a few inside.
Like three cloves.

182
00:08:49,660 --> 00:08:51,330
No, it should be one clove.

183
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:53,130
One clove?

184
00:08:53,130 --> 00:08:56,070
They pop out if there are too many.

185
00:08:58,270 --> 00:09:01,210
That wasn't in our game plan.

186
00:09:01,610 --> 00:09:02,610
I know, right?

187
00:09:02,610 --> 00:09:05,180
I had no idea
you'd give us that type of mortar.

188
00:09:05,550 --> 00:09:07,280
It wasn't even a mortar.

189
00:09:07,980 --> 00:09:09,880
It was smaller than a mug.

190
00:09:10,020 --> 00:09:11,390
They pop out every time.

191
00:09:15,390 --> 00:09:17,460
(Gwan Hee sighs.)

192
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:25,530
The tasks we needed to do
to earn coins were hard.

193
00:09:25,530 --> 00:09:28,540
I've only eaten garlic before,
but I've never peeled it.

194
00:09:31,210 --> 00:09:32,310
Man.

195
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:34,310
Gosh.

196
00:09:35,810 --> 00:09:36,880
Gosh.

197
00:09:38,480 --> 00:09:39,750
This is so stressful.

198
00:09:43,250 --> 00:09:44,750
This is bullcrap.

199
00:09:50,290 --> 00:09:51,530
There's a frog.

200
00:09:52,990 --> 00:09:54,090
All right.

201
00:09:54,560 --> 00:09:56,730
I was like, "Can anyone eat this?"
I just caught it.

202
00:09:57,530 --> 00:09:58,570
There's a frog.

203
00:09:59,700 --> 00:10:01,370
This is insane. We're hunting frogs.

204
00:10:01,370 --> 00:10:03,470
I haven't caught one in 30 years.

205
00:10:03,540 --> 00:10:06,470
Look! There's a huge one!

206
00:10:08,510 --> 00:10:10,510
- Whatever.
- We just have to bring these.

207
00:10:10,510 --> 00:10:13,210
- Whatever.
- Take the potatoes and frogs.

208
00:10:14,110 --> 00:10:16,150
Let's do a chant, guys.

209
00:10:16,550 --> 00:10:17,920
- We'll go down this time.
- Let's go down.

210
00:10:17,920 --> 00:10:19,850
- Rookie, Rookie, Rookie, yes!
- Rookie, Rookie, Rookie, yes!

211
00:10:21,560 --> 00:10:23,720
Don't blame each other,
even if the game doesn't go well.

212
00:10:23,720 --> 00:10:24,860
Of course not.

213
00:10:25,360 --> 00:10:27,900
We'll go all in and win 100 coins in 1 go.

214
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:29,530
Go big or go home.

215
00:10:35,700 --> 00:10:39,240
(They first trade the garlic.)

216
00:10:39,340 --> 00:10:42,340
You get 1 coin for 1kg of crushed garlic.

217
00:10:42,340 --> 00:10:43,680
Let's pour it out and go again.

218
00:10:44,010 --> 00:10:45,910
- It's exactly 1kg.
- Yes.

219
00:10:46,010 --> 00:10:47,920
That's 1kg of crushed garlic.

220
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:49,850
- You will get one coin.
- Yes.

221
00:10:51,990 --> 00:10:53,450
- That's 1kg.
- There we go.

222
00:10:53,450 --> 00:10:55,960
You get 1 coin for 1kg of crushed garlic.

223
00:10:55,960 --> 00:10:57,190
- Yes.
- Thank you.

224
00:10:58,090 --> 00:10:59,590
- Three coins and...
- Frogs.

225
00:10:59,590 --> 00:11:01,400
These guys.

226
00:11:02,360 --> 00:11:03,460
- I'll put it on top.
- Okay.

227
00:11:03,460 --> 00:11:04,630
(Adding the potato they saved up)

228
00:11:04,730 --> 00:11:06,830
- That's 500g.
- The ingredients weigh 500g,

229
00:11:06,830 --> 00:11:08,170
so you will get five coins.

230
00:11:08,640 --> 00:11:11,210
All right. Great job.

231
00:11:11,410 --> 00:11:13,010
- That's 15 coins.
- Will you trade them in?

232
00:11:13,010 --> 00:11:15,180
- Yes. Is that 15 coins?
- Yes, 15 coins. We're ready.

233
00:11:15,940 --> 00:11:17,040
Let's do it.

234
00:11:18,510 --> 00:11:21,450
Today's game at the Ghost Casino is
the Money Bug Game.

235
00:11:21,450 --> 00:11:23,220
Would you like to play?

236
00:11:23,220 --> 00:11:24,320
- Yes.
- Yes. Absolutely.

237
00:11:24,320 --> 00:11:27,050
I will explain the rules
of the Money Bug Game.

238
00:11:28,260 --> 00:11:31,230
The Money Bug Game is a game
where players bet...

239
00:11:31,230 --> 00:11:34,600
on which exit a moving money bug
on a maze board will escape through.

240
00:11:34,830 --> 00:11:37,800
There are a total of six exits
on the maze board,

241
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:40,570
and the width of each exit varies
depending on its payout multiplier.

242
00:11:41,270 --> 00:11:43,900
Players can choose one exit...

243
00:11:44,070 --> 00:11:46,240
and freely bet their coins.

244
00:11:46,570 --> 00:11:47,710
Once the betting is complete,

245
00:11:47,710 --> 00:11:50,210
the directions of the walls
installed on the board are adjusted.

246
00:11:50,410 --> 00:11:52,510
We need a little bit of luck too.

247
00:11:53,280 --> 00:11:56,650
When the game starts,
the money bug is released onto the board.

248
00:11:57,350 --> 00:12:00,390
The game ends as soon as the money bug
successfully escapes...

249
00:12:00,390 --> 00:12:01,690
through any of the exits.

250
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:04,990
If it escapes through the exit
selected by the player,

251
00:12:05,290 --> 00:12:07,530
coins are paid out according
to the corresponding multiplier...

252
00:12:07,530 --> 00:12:08,730
for that exit.

253
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:10,200
It's either of these two.

254
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:11,430
- This is... No.
- It's just luck.

255
00:12:11,430 --> 00:12:13,670
It might not be just luck. Watch.

256
00:12:14,440 --> 00:12:15,570
We can block all the ways.

257
00:12:16,270 --> 00:12:19,270
We can increase our chances
with a few blocks.

258
