2195
01:43:07,650 --> 01:43:11,850
I believe our team
will come in first place.

2196
01:43:11,950 --> 01:43:14,590
That's why taking such a risk
is no big deal for me.

2197
01:43:15,790 --> 01:43:17,260
Let's come in first place today.

2198
01:43:18,030 --> 01:43:20,130
We have to today.

2199
01:43:20,260 --> 01:43:21,860
- Exactly.
- We must show them...

2200
01:43:22,130 --> 01:43:23,930
what we've got so they keep us in check.

2201
01:43:23,930 --> 01:43:25,330
- Or else...
- Right.

2202
01:43:25,330 --> 01:43:28,240
Didn't you mention that
you were good at this game?

2203
01:43:28,240 --> 01:43:30,970
I'm good at storytelling.

2204
01:43:31,770 --> 01:43:35,940
Honestly, I think about weird things
a lot more than others.

2205
01:43:36,180 --> 01:43:40,320
What's more, comedians are pros
when it comes to brainstorming.

2206
01:43:40,520 --> 01:43:41,580
I'm confident.

2207
01:43:41,780 --> 01:43:44,020
I volunteered to do most of the deducing.

2208
01:43:44,020 --> 01:43:46,890
Beom was very confident,

2209
01:43:46,890 --> 01:43:48,520
so I trusted him.

2210
01:43:48,520 --> 01:43:51,130
We should ask as many questions
as possible...

2211
01:43:51,130 --> 01:43:53,560
- without thinking about the time.
- Exactly.

2212
01:43:53,560 --> 01:43:54,630
Asking questions...

2213
01:43:54,630 --> 01:43:57,370
and using as many items as possible
seems like a good plan.

2214
01:43:57,670 --> 01:43:59,770
- Simply put, for example...
- Yes?

2215
01:43:59,770 --> 01:44:01,040
- Have faith in me.
- We...

2216
01:44:01,040 --> 01:44:02,640
I'm the MC of "Surprise: Mystery Salon."

2217
01:44:02,640 --> 01:44:04,110
"Surprise: Mystery Salon."

2218
01:44:04,110 --> 01:44:05,940
I bet the others are bad at it.

2219
01:44:07,910 --> 01:44:11,280
You think there's no need to ask
a lot of questions?

2220
01:44:11,280 --> 01:44:13,950
I'm not saying
asking a lot of questions is bad.

2221
01:44:13,950 --> 01:44:15,780
If you think it's fine to ask a lot,

2222
01:44:15,780 --> 01:44:17,990
- There's no end to it?
- there's no end to it.

2223
01:44:17,990 --> 01:44:20,790
Ultimately, it'll lead us
to contradicting ourselves.

2224
01:44:21,260 --> 01:44:22,860
Let's not go in without a plan.

2225
01:44:23,120 --> 01:44:26,260
Who, what, when, where, why, and how.

2226
01:44:26,530 --> 01:44:28,530
Think of it as figuring out
those six questions...

2227
01:44:28,530 --> 01:44:29,900
as we narrow down the keywords.

2228
01:44:29,900 --> 01:44:32,400
That's a faster way to get the answer.

2229
01:44:32,800 --> 01:44:34,870
- This is our kind of game...
- Yes?

2230
01:44:34,870 --> 01:44:36,240
- to begin with.
- True.

2231
01:44:36,240 --> 01:44:37,910
- Yes, it is.
- We know we'll do well.

2232
01:44:38,070 --> 01:44:41,880
There's no need to ask the other teams
to work with us first.

2233
01:44:41,880 --> 01:44:42,940
- I bet they'll ask first.
- Exactly.

2234
01:44:42,940 --> 01:44:44,010
So let's not share...

2235
01:44:44,480 --> 01:44:46,620
- information with the others.
- Okay.

2236
01:44:46,620 --> 01:44:49,520
If we're in a situation
where we'll come in...

2237
01:44:49,520 --> 01:44:51,320
first or second place,

2238
01:44:51,650 --> 01:44:53,020
we could earn brownie points...

2239
01:44:53,020 --> 01:44:55,220
- before finishing the game.
- Right.

2240
01:44:55,220 --> 01:44:56,390
- Then...
- Let's give them that...

2241
01:44:56,390 --> 01:44:58,630
but try to work it out among our team.

2242
01:44:59,060 --> 01:45:00,700
Why don't we come to an agreement?

2243
01:45:00,700 --> 01:45:03,570
- Either way, we must...
- Are you free?

2244
01:45:03,570 --> 01:45:06,640
- Yes.
- Before the game starts,

2245
01:45:06,640 --> 01:45:07,670
our team wants to clarify...

2246
01:45:07,670 --> 01:45:09,100
- everyone's interests first.
- Got it.

2247
01:45:09,570 --> 01:45:12,010
Let's make sure we're on the same page...

2248
01:45:12,270 --> 01:45:14,910
- about giving and taking...
- Promise.

2249
01:45:14,910 --> 01:45:17,680
regarding how we helped you out yesterday.

2250
01:45:18,210 --> 01:45:20,580
Firstly, from our perspective,

2251
01:45:20,580 --> 01:45:23,320
the best option is...

2252
01:45:23,520 --> 01:45:25,690
to work together...

2253
01:45:25,850 --> 01:45:28,260
as one team...

2254
01:45:28,260 --> 01:45:30,360
and let us win.

2255
01:45:31,490 --> 01:45:33,630
- That's right.
- You've got the premise wrong.

2256
01:45:33,630 --> 01:45:35,960
- Yes?
- We made it clear yesterday.

2257
01:45:36,200 --> 01:45:38,130
We didn't team up with you...

2258
01:45:38,130 --> 01:45:40,340
- so that Team P2 could win.
- I see.

2259
01:45:40,340 --> 01:45:43,240
We teamed up to win together as one team.

2260
01:45:43,240 --> 01:45:44,910
That was our premise.

2261
01:45:44,910 --> 01:45:46,070
No, that's not true.

2262
01:45:46,070 --> 01:45:47,840
- What? No.
- No.

2263
01:45:48,480 --> 01:45:49,940
- Round One...
- Who did you talk with?

2264
01:45:49,940 --> 01:45:51,380
- Xitsuh.
- What?

2265
01:45:51,380 --> 01:45:52,550
He said we'd help you win?

2266
01:45:52,550 --> 01:45:53,750
Right? Say that you did.

2267
01:45:56,920 --> 01:45:58,290
(During last night's Money Challenge)

2268
01:45:58,290 --> 01:46:00,290
We'll act as the kingmaker.

2269
01:46:00,690 --> 01:46:04,160
But in return,
make sure you keep our alliance.

2270
01:46:04,530 --> 01:46:05,530
- Okay.
- If possible.

2271
01:46:05,530 --> 01:46:08,330
- Right.
- All I can guarantee...

2272
01:46:08,330 --> 01:46:09,500
is a verbal promise.

2273
01:46:09,500 --> 01:46:10,570
Tomorrow's main match.

2274
01:46:10,570 --> 01:46:11,700
Okay, tomorrow's main match.

2275
01:46:11,700 --> 01:46:13,700
This is the only way to form an alliance.

2276
01:46:13,700 --> 01:46:15,570
- Someone has to sacrifice.
- Only one team can win.

2277
01:46:15,570 --> 01:46:18,040
A deal can be made
only when one side sacrifices...

2278
01:46:18,040 --> 01:46:19,210
and promises the next match.

2279
01:46:19,210 --> 01:46:20,510
If you help us out this time,

2280
01:46:20,780 --> 01:46:22,510
we'll return the favor in the next game.

2281
01:46:22,510 --> 01:46:24,110
- Two games.
- Right.

2282
01:46:24,510 --> 01:46:25,710
Right? Say that you did.

2283
01:46:25,710 --> 01:46:26,950
Yes, I did.

2284
01:46:26,950 --> 01:46:28,620
But when we were together,

2285
01:46:28,620 --> 01:46:30,220
Jin Ho changed his mind.

2286
01:46:30,220 --> 01:46:31,450
That's the order of events.

2287
01:46:32,120 --> 01:46:33,620
This is the first time I'm hearing this.

2288
01:46:33,620 --> 01:46:35,860
Even if you think about it right now,

2289
01:46:35,860 --> 01:46:37,590
we helped you out in that game.

2290
01:46:37,590 --> 01:46:39,260
The kingmaker game.

2291
01:46:39,260 --> 01:46:42,060
Then this is something
we could rightfully ask you to do.

2292
01:46:42,060 --> 01:46:44,570
- You totally can. I simply wanted...
- Right?

2293
01:46:44,570 --> 01:46:47,600
to tell you the order
in which things happened.

2294
01:46:47,600 --> 01:46:48,700
He didn't want to keep his promise.

2295
01:46:48,700 --> 01:46:49,840
He already got what he wanted.

2296
01:46:49,840 --> 01:46:51,310
What's more, it's not a clear-cut game.

2297
01:46:51,310 --> 01:46:53,540
It's not a game
where you can get full support.

2298
01:46:54,080 --> 01:46:56,110
So, they didn't agree on it.

2299
01:46:56,310 --> 01:46:59,250
Even so, Xitsuh should've stepped up.

2300
01:46:59,250 --> 01:47:01,750
But Jin Ho hadn't heard anything
from Xitsuh.

2301
01:47:01,750 --> 01:47:04,050
Xitsuh kept quiet.

2302
01:47:04,050 --> 01:47:05,850
It was underhanded and a hateful sight.

2303
01:47:06,090 --> 01:47:08,260
From what I remember,

2304
01:47:08,260 --> 01:47:09,260
the last person...

2305
01:47:09,260 --> 01:47:10,990
- I spoke to yesterday was Jin Hyeong.
- Me.

2306
01:47:10,990 --> 01:47:12,730
Here's what I heard.

2307
01:47:12,730 --> 01:47:14,800
I constantly told you
I wasn't the decision maker.

2308
01:47:14,800 --> 01:47:16,870
Right. Seung Jin was with us back then.

2309
01:47:16,870 --> 01:47:18,570
- Yes, everyone was there.
- When we talked,

2310
01:47:18,570 --> 01:47:20,640
we all agreed and made a deal.

2311
01:47:20,640 --> 01:47:21,770
- In Team P2's room...
- The chat...

2312
01:47:21,770 --> 01:47:23,440
I don't remember agreeing to it.

2313
01:47:23,770 --> 01:47:25,610
- But...
- I heard that, but I...

2314
01:47:26,410 --> 01:47:27,810
(The conversation
after making a deal with Xitsuh)

2315
01:47:27,810 --> 01:47:30,410
What we're looking for
is an unbreakable alliance.

2316
01:47:30,710 --> 01:47:31,710
That's all we want.

2317
01:47:32,110 --> 01:47:33,980
Do you want our help,
or do you want to win together?

2318
01:47:35,680 --> 01:47:37,520
Can't you help us while working together?

2319
01:47:38,090 --> 01:47:39,450
Helping means...

2320
01:47:39,450 --> 01:47:41,090
our working as kingmakers to make you win.

2321
01:47:41,090 --> 01:47:42,990
- That's too one-sided.
- What do you think?

2322
01:47:42,990 --> 01:47:44,330
Since Seung Jin is the one sacrificing,

2323
01:47:44,330 --> 01:47:45,560
his opinion matters.

2324
01:47:45,690 --> 01:47:46,960
The game is going to change tomorrow,

2325
01:47:46,960 --> 01:47:48,800
so I'm not asking for it,
no questions asked.

2326
01:47:48,800 --> 01:47:50,570
What we can promise...

2327
01:47:50,570 --> 01:47:52,030
- is to work together tomorrow.
- Yes.

2328
01:47:52,030 --> 01:47:53,030
Just keep that promise.

2329
01:47:53,030 --> 01:47:54,640
- That's more than enough.
- Okay.

2330
01:47:56,240 --> 01:47:58,040
I couldn't believe the other team.

2331
01:47:58,440 --> 01:48:00,780
When I asked Jin Hyeong
if he remembered our talk,

2332
01:48:00,780 --> 01:48:02,940
he tried to get out of it.

2333
01:48:02,940 --> 01:48:04,480
It was very irresponsible.

2334
01:48:05,280 --> 01:48:07,450
But what's funny is that...

2335
01:48:07,450 --> 01:48:09,220
Xitsuh isn't our team's decision-maker.

2336
01:48:09,220 --> 01:48:10,220
It's me.

2337
01:48:10,450 --> 01:48:13,560
What you want is
for us to sacrifice in Round One...

2338
01:48:13,560 --> 01:48:16,220
- and help Team P2 come in 1st place?
- Yes.

2339
01:48:16,220 --> 01:48:19,030
In our shoes, in a kingmaker game,

2340
01:48:19,230 --> 01:48:22,030
we basically did charity work.

2341
01:48:22,030 --> 01:48:23,900
- So before the game starts...
- Either way,

2342
01:48:23,900 --> 01:48:24,930
we need to find a middle ground.

2343
01:48:24,930 --> 01:48:26,270
- Correct.
- A kingmaker is out of the question...

2344
01:48:26,270 --> 01:48:27,470
- in my opinion.
- I see.

2345
01:48:27,470 --> 01:48:28,700
Having eight members.

2346
01:48:28,700 --> 01:48:31,070
Having too many heads
isn't always helpful.

2347
01:48:32,370 --> 01:48:33,740
Isn't it weird?

2348
01:48:34,940 --> 01:48:36,640
- May I say a word?
- Go ahead.

2349
01:48:36,640 --> 01:48:38,350
We're in the same situation as yesterday,

2350
01:48:38,350 --> 01:48:40,080
so what wasn't weird about yesterday
and is weird about today?

2351
01:48:40,080 --> 01:48:41,180
Here's what I want to know.

2352
01:48:41,180 --> 01:48:43,020
How do you want us to help you?

2353
01:48:43,020 --> 01:48:44,490
There will be twice as many questions,

2354
01:48:44,490 --> 01:48:45,890
while the same amount of time
will be deducted,

2355
01:48:45,890 --> 01:48:47,160
since there are eight of us.

2356
01:48:47,160 --> 01:48:49,390
Naturally, we'll have twice
as many questions.

2357
01:48:49,390 --> 01:48:50,790
- But failing to win...
- More information?

2358
01:48:50,790 --> 01:48:53,230
with twice as many questions
would be our fault.

2359
01:48:53,500 --> 01:48:55,460
We'll have twice as much information.

2360
01:48:56,800 --> 01:48:58,530
We worked as one team yesterday.

2361
01:48:58,530 --> 01:48:59,970
You agree on that, right?

2362
01:49:00,400 --> 01:49:02,500
Whether it's 2, 4, or 8 people,

2363
01:49:02,500 --> 01:49:04,170
the efficiency won't change drastically.

2364
01:49:04,170 --> 01:49:06,880
It could make things more efficient
or less efficient.

2365
01:49:06,880 --> 01:49:08,940
There's a possibility
that the efficiency could improve.

2366
01:49:08,940 --> 01:49:11,410
This is a game in which too many cooks...

2367
01:49:11,410 --> 01:49:14,180
- could spoil the broth.
- I understand.

2368
01:49:14,180 --> 01:49:15,780
That's what I'm concerned about.

2369
01:49:15,780 --> 01:49:18,120
What we want is twice as many cooks,

2370
01:49:18,120 --> 01:49:19,850
not to cook the broth well.

2371
01:49:19,850 --> 01:49:21,490
I simply want twice as many cooks.

2372
01:49:21,490 --> 01:49:23,630
That's not the deal I remember we made.

2373
01:49:23,630 --> 01:49:25,860
You recall what I said, don't you?

2374
01:49:25,860 --> 01:49:27,030
You were there with me.

2375
01:49:27,030 --> 01:49:28,130
I do recall it,

2376
01:49:28,130 --> 01:49:30,130
- but...
- Here's the thing.

2377
01:49:30,130 --> 01:49:31,970
You're saying, "I heard what you said,"

2378
01:49:31,970 --> 01:49:34,140
"but as I wasn't the decision-maker,
I didn't agree to it."

2379
01:49:34,140 --> 01:49:36,870
You're acting very irresponsibly.

2380
01:49:36,870 --> 01:49:39,440
I wouldn't have proceeded with the plan...

2381
01:49:39,440 --> 01:49:42,110
if either you or Seung Jin...

2382
01:49:42,110 --> 01:49:44,580
hadn't shown interest in the deal.

2383
01:49:44,580 --> 01:49:47,180
I was for working together,

2384
01:49:47,180 --> 01:49:49,020
not becoming a kingmaker.

2385
01:49:49,020 --> 01:49:50,990
That's why I agreed to the plan.

2386
01:49:50,990 --> 01:49:53,720
Either way, we agreed upon something...

2387
01:49:53,720 --> 01:49:55,520
and worked together.

2388
01:49:55,520 --> 01:49:57,490
But coming here now,

2389
01:49:57,830 --> 01:49:59,830
telling us to take full responsibility
and help you come in first place...

2390
01:49:59,830 --> 01:50:01,060
since Xitsuh is on our team...

2391
01:50:01,060 --> 01:50:03,160
is a bit... As a member of this team,

2392
01:50:03,160 --> 01:50:05,470
I spoke with you about it.

2393
01:50:05,470 --> 01:50:07,470
I was part of it.

2394
01:50:07,470 --> 01:50:09,100
But saying that what I said is invalid...

2395
01:50:09,100 --> 01:50:11,370
while what you said is valid is weird.

2396
01:50:11,610 --> 01:50:14,310
Jin Ho is making all kinds of excuses.
But the main point is that...

2397
01:50:14,310 --> 01:50:16,440
his team can't help us
come in first place...

2398
01:50:16,440 --> 01:50:18,450
even though we were their kingmaker
yesterday.

2399
01:50:18,450 --> 01:50:19,580
Honestly, I wasn't shocked.

2400
01:50:19,580 --> 01:50:20,980
It's nothing new in this place.

2401
01:50:20,980 --> 01:50:22,820
Trusting each other would make you a fool.

2402
01:50:22,980 --> 01:50:25,650
Even so, Team P3 acting like that...

2403
01:50:25,990 --> 01:50:27,390
did upset me.

2404
01:50:28,120 --> 01:50:30,220
- Let's balance it out.
- Okay.

2405
01:50:30,690 --> 01:50:33,700
There's no need to tell us
the information...

2406
01:50:33,930 --> 01:50:35,500
- you get.
- Got it.

2407
01:50:35,500 --> 01:50:37,670
But our team will share a portion
of the information,

2408
01:50:37,670 --> 01:50:39,470
- whether it be keywords, with you.
- Just a portion is fine.

2409
01:50:39,470 --> 01:50:41,200
We'll even things out like this
for Round One.

2410
01:50:41,200 --> 01:50:42,200
- Okay.
- If you get first place,

2411
01:50:42,200 --> 01:50:43,270
- the deal ends there.
- Right.

2412
01:50:43,270 --> 01:50:44,470
If you don't...

2413
01:50:44,470 --> 01:50:46,370
and get the chance to spend money,

2414
01:50:46,370 --> 01:50:47,840
we'll support you financially up to
a certain amount.

2415
01:50:47,840 --> 01:50:49,180
- All right.
- That's how far we'll go.

2416
01:50:49,410 --> 01:50:50,980
Giving you limitless support...

2417
01:50:50,980 --> 01:50:52,310
- No.
- as a kingmaker is a bit...

2418
01:50:52,510 --> 01:50:53,510
- That's enough.
- Okay.

2419
01:50:53,510 --> 01:50:54,880
It's clear that you helped us,

2420
01:50:54,880 --> 01:50:57,290
- so it's only fair to return the favor.
- Right.

2421
01:50:57,750 --> 01:50:59,650
- Okay for now.
- Great.

2422
01:50:59,750 --> 01:51:01,090
- I'll see you later. Bye.
- Bye.

2423
01:51:01,090 --> 01:51:02,590
- Good luck.
- Are we done?

2424
01:51:02,590 --> 01:51:04,260
- We're done.
- There wasn't much to talk about.

2425
01:51:04,260 --> 01:51:05,430
In Round One,

2426
01:51:05,930 --> 01:51:09,830
we won't receive any information
from Team P2.

2427
01:51:09,900 --> 01:51:11,870
However, if our team finds something out,

2428
01:51:11,970 --> 01:51:14,340
we will share a lot with Team P2.

2429
01:51:14,340 --> 01:51:16,540
If there comes a situation
where we have to use...

2430
01:51:16,540 --> 01:51:18,340
the elimination immunity pass
or the vote ticket,

2431
01:51:18,570 --> 01:51:19,570
we'll use it.

2432
01:51:20,170 --> 01:51:22,780
That was the agreement we reached.

2433
01:51:23,110 --> 01:51:25,480
Okay, that team will share information
with us.

2434
01:51:27,520 --> 01:51:29,850
But if they have the chance
to come in first place,

2435
01:51:29,850 --> 01:51:31,020
they'd choose to win.

2436
01:51:31,290 --> 01:51:33,120
That's inevitable.

2437
01:51:33,120 --> 01:51:34,190
It's beyond our control.

2438
01:51:34,190 --> 01:51:35,190
- True.
- From what I see...

2439
01:51:35,190 --> 01:51:36,960
They're going to control
how much help they give us.

2440
01:51:36,960 --> 01:51:39,190
Just enough so that it doesn't
get in the way of them winning.

2441
01:51:39,730 --> 01:51:40,800
It's only natural.

2442
01:51:40,800 --> 01:51:42,330
- True.
- What we can do...

2443
01:51:42,330 --> 01:51:44,130
Xitsuh didn't say a word.

2444
01:51:44,130 --> 01:51:45,300
Xitsuh, he...

2445
01:51:45,970 --> 01:51:48,070
- It's absurd.
- Of course.

2446
01:51:48,070 --> 01:51:49,540
We're cutting him some slack here.

2447
01:51:49,540 --> 01:51:50,540
Exactly.

2448
01:51:50,870 --> 01:51:52,470
The team will give us information...

2449
01:51:52,470 --> 01:51:54,140
that's useless to them.

2450
01:51:54,140 --> 01:51:55,340
It's plain obvious.

2451
01:51:55,340 --> 01:51:57,680
But as promised,
they need to give us money if we ask.

2452
01:51:57,680 --> 01:52:00,480
That's not even a quarter
of how much we helped them.

2453
01:52:01,480 --> 01:52:02,780
(The end of the strategy meeting)

2454
01:52:02,780 --> 01:52:04,850
Please gather in the main hall.

2455
01:52:04,850 --> 01:52:06,390
(The end of the strategy meeting)

2456
01:52:06,650 --> 01:52:08,290
Can't we just...

2457
01:52:08,290 --> 01:52:09,620
go to sleep after Round One?

2458
01:52:09,860 --> 01:52:10,890
Look at that confidence in ending it...

2459
01:52:10,890 --> 01:52:12,760
- at Round One.
- Come on.

2460
01:52:13,130 --> 01:52:15,030
He's full of himself. What a wacko.

2461
01:52:16,460 --> 01:52:19,300
Ji Min, that's what we also thought.

2462
01:52:21,170 --> 01:52:23,270
Checking the keywords...

2463
01:52:23,910 --> 01:52:27,410
Today's Money Challenge,
Mystery Time, will now begin.

2464
01:52:28,310 --> 01:52:31,010
Items are up for sale starting now.

2465
01:52:38,190 --> 01:52:39,450
Are you out of your mind?

2466
01:52:41,520 --> 01:52:42,660
Are you out of your mind?

2467
01:52:45,390 --> 01:52:47,260
I'd like to buy a keyword reveal pass.

2468
01:52:47,260 --> 01:52:50,400
For Team P1, 10,000 dollars
will be deducted from the team funds.

2469
01:52:50,770 --> 01:52:52,770
I'd like to buy a keyword reveal pass.

2470
01:52:52,770 --> 01:52:55,140
I'd like to buy one keyword reveal pass.

2471
01:52:55,570 --> 01:52:58,170
Here's the image and question
for Round One.

2472
01:52:58,940 --> 01:53:01,580
Round One has five correct keywords.

2473
01:53:02,710 --> 01:53:06,280
Electrician Mark was found dead
at a client's home.

2474
01:53:06,580 --> 01:53:08,050
What really happened?

2475
01:53:08,050 --> 01:53:09,420
(Electrician Mark was found dead
at a client's home.)

2476
01:53:09,420 --> 01:53:10,490
(What really happened?)

2477
01:53:10,490 --> 01:53:11,690
(5 keywords)

2478
01:53:11,920 --> 01:53:15,120
First off,
we have electrician Mark and his client.

2479
01:53:15,360 --> 01:53:17,020
Is the client not so important?

2480
01:53:17,230 --> 01:53:19,390
They don't even have a name.

2481
01:53:20,030 --> 01:53:21,160
In such a case,

2482
01:53:21,400 --> 01:53:26,270
the woman might be Mark, not the man.

2483
01:53:26,530 --> 01:53:29,000
Or the woman could be Mark,
but not the client.

2484
01:53:29,600 --> 01:53:30,770
We have to keep that in mind.

2485
01:53:32,370 --> 01:53:35,180
It was important to pinpoint
which one was Mark.

2486
01:53:35,180 --> 01:53:37,210
Mark might not even be in the image.

2487
01:53:37,580 --> 01:53:40,280
Whether it's the Caucasian man
or the African-American lady in the image.

2488
01:53:46,020 --> 01:53:48,290
Is Mark the Caucasian man?

2489
01:53:49,260 --> 01:53:50,490
Yes, that is correct.

2490
01:53:51,130 --> 01:53:53,330
Is the client the African-American woman?

2491
01:53:54,260 --> 01:53:55,500
Yes, that is correct.

2492
01:53:56,830 --> 01:54:00,900
Is there any other person not in the image
who is related to the death?

2493
01:54:03,370 --> 01:54:04,710
Yes, that is correct.

2494
01:54:05,070 --> 01:54:06,070
Thank you.

2495
01:54:06,070 --> 01:54:08,340
(Park Ji Min:
3 extra minutes for asking 3 questions)

2496
01:54:11,810 --> 01:54:15,550
The questions early in the game
could be all sorts,

2497
01:54:15,550 --> 01:54:16,550
so I'm going to ask...

2498
01:54:16,550 --> 01:54:17,950
- Okay.
- three appropriate questions.

2499
01:54:18,890 --> 01:54:20,620
Is this to buy an item or what?

2500
01:54:20,620 --> 01:54:21,620
To buy an item.

2501
01:54:21,820 --> 01:54:22,960
To buy an item?

2502
01:54:22,960 --> 01:54:24,290
(There's a line before the Voting Room.)

2503
01:54:24,290 --> 01:54:25,430
I have a question.

2504
01:54:25,830 --> 01:54:27,500
- The question line.
- Is this the question line?

2505
01:54:27,500 --> 01:54:29,360
- Guys. YunB and Sung Joo.
- Yes?

2506
01:54:29,360 --> 01:54:31,070
I think it's best to get in line first.

2507
01:54:31,570 --> 01:54:32,570
Get in line.

2508
01:54:33,000 --> 01:54:34,040
What a long line.

2509
01:54:35,540 --> 01:54:37,040
One person must stay in the pantry.

2510
01:54:37,040 --> 01:54:38,210
Take a seat.

2511
01:54:40,780 --> 01:54:43,510
The first question would be about
whether it's an accident or not.

2512
01:54:43,510 --> 01:54:45,980
How about asking if it's murder?

2513
01:54:45,980 --> 01:54:47,380
An accidental death is my top choice.

2514
01:54:47,380 --> 01:54:49,950
Suicide and murder
do not fall under accidental death.

2515
01:54:50,590 --> 01:54:52,320
Accidental death
does not include suicide or murder.

2516
01:54:52,320 --> 01:54:53,720
So you want to ask if it was an accident?

2517
01:54:53,720 --> 01:54:55,090
- Yes, an accidental death.
- Okay.

2518
01:54:55,090 --> 01:54:56,520
We should ask right away.

2519
01:55:02,560 --> 01:55:03,830
Is someone in there?

2520
01:55:03,830 --> 01:55:04,830
Yes.

2521
01:55:10,500 --> 01:55:11,610
Let's get in line.

2522
01:55:12,710 --> 01:55:15,340
As there are no penalties
for asking questions,

2523
01:55:15,610 --> 01:55:17,950
