The Dubai chewy cookie was low in stock.

2529
01:55:30,930 --> 01:55:33,900
We belatedly sent people to line up,

2530
01:55:33,900 --> 01:55:37,400
but we were the 9th or 10th in line.
One of the last questioners.

2531
01:55:37,400 --> 01:55:40,200
The penalty of asking many questions
doesn't matter...

2532
01:55:40,200 --> 01:55:41,640
as long as you come in first place.

2533
01:55:41,640 --> 01:55:43,270
Even if you ask tons of questions,

2534
01:55:43,270 --> 01:55:45,510
what matters is getting
as many truthful facts as possible.

2535
01:55:45,510 --> 01:55:46,640
So get in line, period.

2536
01:55:46,640 --> 01:55:48,040
What else should we ask?

2537
01:55:48,340 --> 01:55:49,710
- Those guys.
- Yes?

2538
01:55:49,710 --> 01:55:52,250
They don't even care who was in the room.

2539
01:55:52,250 --> 01:55:54,320
Once you come out of the room,
I'll leave the line.

2540
01:55:54,920 --> 01:55:56,080
- Got it.
- You do, right?

2541
01:55:56,080 --> 01:55:57,450
You two should go in twice, okay?

2542
01:55:57,450 --> 01:55:58,450
Okay.

2543
01:55:59,150 --> 01:56:01,490
Was Mark's death accidental?

2544
01:56:03,490 --> 01:56:04,790
Yes, that is correct.

2545
01:56:06,230 --> 01:56:08,860
Did Mark die from electric shock?

2546
01:56:08,860 --> 01:56:10,870
(Did Mark die from electric shock?)

2547
01:56:10,870 --> 01:56:12,500
No, that is incorrect.

2548
01:56:13,470 --> 01:56:17,740
Did Mark die from eating food offered...

2549
01:56:18,110 --> 01:56:20,710
by someone not in the image?

2550
01:56:20,710 --> 01:56:22,310
No, that is incorrect.

2551
01:56:22,580 --> 01:56:24,750
(As soon as Tae Gyun
walks out of the room,)

2552
01:56:24,750 --> 01:56:28,020
(Sang Min leaves the line.)

2553
01:56:28,550 --> 01:56:32,390
(Entering again)

2554
01:56:33,220 --> 01:56:36,260
Did Mark die...

2555
01:56:36,260 --> 01:56:38,630
from an allergic reaction?

2556
01:56:39,930 --> 01:56:41,760
No, that is incorrect.

2557
01:56:42,400 --> 01:56:43,660
What do I ask?

2558
01:56:44,900 --> 01:56:45,900
This one?

2559
01:56:47,440 --> 01:56:48,440
Gosh.

2560
01:56:49,470 --> 01:56:50,470
Hi.

2561
01:56:51,910 --> 01:56:52,940
Did...

2562
01:56:54,010 --> 01:56:55,710
Mark die from an accident?

2563
01:56:56,980 --> 01:56:58,280
Yes, that is correct.

2564
01:56:58,280 --> 01:56:59,280
For real?

2565
01:56:59,280 --> 01:57:02,120
A good question does not get you
the answer.

2566
01:57:02,120 --> 01:57:04,690
Regardless of whether the answer
is "yes" or "no,"

2567
01:57:04,690 --> 01:57:07,360
it should be a question where you can get
the most information out of it.

2568
01:57:07,360 --> 01:57:09,190
Like doing a binary search in math.

2569
01:57:09,190 --> 01:57:11,060
Calling the middle number, 50,

2570
01:57:11,060 --> 01:57:13,260
and asking
whether it's higher or lower than 50.

2571
01:57:13,260 --> 01:57:14,400
You narrow down the range by half.

2572
01:57:14,400 --> 01:57:16,060
From there, you call 25,

2573
01:57:16,060 --> 01:57:17,730
ask whether it's higher or lower than it,

2574
01:57:17,730 --> 01:57:18,800
and narrow down the range by half again.

2575
01:57:19,000 --> 01:57:21,740
You must find the answer
by narrowing down the range step by step.

2576
01:57:21,740 --> 01:57:26,540
Did Mark visit the client's house
to fix something?

2577
01:57:28,240 --> 01:57:29,810
No, that is incorrect.

2578
01:57:30,780 --> 01:57:32,850
Since it wasn't to fix something,

2579
01:57:32,850 --> 01:57:35,280
he could've visited
for a different reason.

2580
01:57:35,580 --> 01:57:39,290
Did Mark visit the client's house...

2581
01:57:40,250 --> 01:57:43,220
to commit a crime?

2582
01:57:46,860 --> 01:57:48,160
Yes, that is correct.

2583
01:57:48,900 --> 01:57:49,900
Goodness.

2584
01:57:51,470 --> 01:57:52,770
I got the answer.

2585
01:57:53,630 --> 01:57:54,640
Really?

2586
01:57:54,640 --> 01:57:56,170
- What was the question?
- What was it?

2587
01:57:56,670 --> 01:57:57,770
Did you get something big?

2588
01:57:58,470 --> 01:57:59,810
- Show me.
- I see.

2589
01:57:59,810 --> 01:58:01,480
- Do you have your questions?
- Me.

2590
01:58:01,480 --> 01:58:03,040
Mark didn't visit to fix things,

2591
01:58:03,040 --> 01:58:04,280
and it was an accidental death.

2592
01:58:04,280 --> 01:58:06,480
We can find out what accident it was
once we know where he died.

2593
01:58:08,850 --> 01:58:09,950
Did Mark...

2594
01:58:12,890 --> 01:58:15,690
die in a different room,
not in the living room?

2595
01:58:19,160 --> 01:58:20,430
Yes, that is correct.

2596
01:58:21,560 --> 01:58:24,200
I asked the biggest question.

2597
01:58:24,200 --> 01:58:25,730
I narrowed down from there.

2598
01:58:27,640 --> 01:58:29,270
When I asked if Mark had died
in a different room...

2599
01:58:29,270 --> 01:58:30,940
and not in the living room,

2600
01:58:30,940 --> 01:58:33,370
- she said yes.
- The first question?

2601
01:58:33,370 --> 01:58:35,510
- So where he died also matters.
- Let's drop by.

2602
01:58:43,550 --> 01:58:44,550
Seong Beom.

2603
01:58:49,390 --> 01:58:51,090
The electrician came.

2604
01:58:52,360 --> 01:58:53,760
But why aren't the lights out?

2605
01:58:53,760 --> 01:58:56,100
In the image, the lamp was on.

2606
01:58:57,430 --> 01:58:58,430
So why did he come by?

2607
01:58:58,600 --> 01:59:00,700
Did he not come to fix the electricity?

2608
01:59:00,700 --> 01:59:03,000
Or did only a certain area black out?

2609
01:59:03,000 --> 01:59:04,610
I looked at the image,
and the door was open.

2610
01:59:04,610 --> 01:59:07,240
Beyond the door, it was pitch black.

2611
01:59:07,610 --> 01:59:11,250
It seemed like an entrance to a room.

2612
01:59:11,250 --> 01:59:12,910
Something must've happened in there.

2613
01:59:13,750 --> 01:59:16,820
Listen, I think I found the hint
inside the image.

2614
01:59:17,490 --> 01:59:18,890
- The door in the back is open, right?
- Yes.

2615
01:59:19,250 --> 01:59:20,990
It's pitch black inside.

2616
01:59:21,360 --> 01:59:22,460
Either the electricity went down
in that room,

2617
01:59:22,460 --> 01:59:23,560
or it's the basement.

2618
01:59:23,560 --> 01:59:25,690
- Right.
- His death must be related to that room.

2619
01:59:25,690 --> 01:59:28,200
We must eliminate the big questions.

2620
01:59:28,630 --> 01:59:30,900
The problem is that
all the doors are open.

2621
01:59:30,900 --> 01:59:32,200
I'm most concerned about that.

2622
01:59:32,700 --> 01:59:34,400
- The points I saw were...
- Yes?

2623
01:59:35,000 --> 01:59:36,800
Here's the room.

2624
01:59:37,540 --> 01:59:38,870
- There are two doors.
- Right.

2625
01:59:38,870 --> 01:59:41,580
Day and night. It's weird.

2626
01:59:41,580 --> 01:59:43,480
- In the same space?
- Yes.

2627
01:59:43,910 --> 01:59:46,050
The right door is black.

2628
01:59:46,350 --> 01:59:49,350
But it could be a door
to the dark outside...

2629
01:59:49,350 --> 01:59:51,650
or a door to somewhere else.

2630
01:59:51,650 --> 01:59:53,550
But the entrance door shows
that it's daytime.

2631
01:59:53,550 --> 01:59:55,560
So it's not a door to the night...

2632
01:59:55,560 --> 01:59:58,130
but a door to somewhere dark.

2633
01:59:58,130 --> 02:00:01,560
Is the black area
on the right side of the image...

2634
02:00:01,560 --> 02:00:03,960
a door to the basement?

2635
02:00:06,670 --> 02:00:07,940
Yes, that is correct.

2636
02:00:08,800 --> 02:00:11,510
Did electrician Mark
go to the client's house...

2637
02:00:11,510 --> 02:00:13,340
to fix something?

2638
02:00:13,940 --> 02:00:15,440
No, that is incorrect.

2639
02:00:16,710 --> 02:00:20,050
Did Mark die in the basement...

2640
02:00:20,050 --> 02:00:24,250
that's visible on the right of the image?

2641
02:00:24,850 --> 02:00:27,720
Did Mark die in the basement?

2642
02:00:28,160 --> 02:00:29,290
Did Mark...

2643
02:00:30,160 --> 02:00:33,190
die in the basement?

2644
02:00:36,860 --> 02:00:38,170
Yes, that is correct.

2645
02:00:38,330 --> 02:00:39,400
Okay.

2646
02:00:40,600 --> 02:00:44,340
(Round 1 Keyword: Basement)

2647
02:00:49,680 --> 02:00:51,380
The Time Room is now open.

2648
02:00:51,950 --> 02:00:54,420
- The first image hint is revealed.
- I'll go.

2649
02:00:54,550 --> 02:00:56,680
- I'll go.
- Xitsuh.

2650
02:00:56,680 --> 02:00:57,990
(The Time Room opens
30 minutes after the game starts.)

2651
02:00:59,750 --> 02:01:02,460
(Main hall)

2652
02:01:02,460 --> 02:01:03,460
I'll be back.

2653
02:01:03,460 --> 02:01:05,830
(Time Room on the 4th floor)

2654
02:01:06,460 --> 02:01:08,000
- We can go together.
- Yes.

2655
02:01:08,000 --> 02:01:09,700
- But why are we running?
- I don't plan on outrunning you.

2656
02:01:09,700 --> 02:01:11,400
- Let's go together then.
- Let's go together.

2657
02:01:11,400 --> 02:01:12,700
I'm not going to outrun you.

2658
02:01:12,870 --> 02:01:13,870
Gosh.

2659
02:01:16,800 --> 02:01:19,410
I bet all the questions I asked
will show up as images.

2660
02:01:19,970 --> 02:01:21,810
The pantry. This way.

2661
02:01:29,750 --> 02:01:31,490
- My legs hurt.
- This is tiring.

2662
02:01:38,060 --> 02:01:39,060
Come in.

2663
02:01:39,460 --> 02:01:40,860
Once you enter the Time Room,

2664
02:01:40,860 --> 02:01:42,700
- you cannot take notes.
- Okay.

2665
02:01:42,700 --> 02:01:44,060
Also, once you enter the Time Room,

2666
02:01:44,060 --> 02:01:46,570
your personal time will be accumulated
twice as much.

2667
02:01:53,240 --> 02:01:54,240
What's this?

2668
02:01:58,380 --> 02:01:59,950
It was in the evening.

2669
02:02:00,780 --> 02:02:02,720
And the client was sleeping.

2670
02:02:03,050 --> 02:02:05,690
The most important thing is,
the door was closed.

2671
02:02:05,690 --> 02:02:08,090
Mark cried for help,

2672
02:02:08,090 --> 02:02:09,360
but she didn't hear him
because she was asleep.

2673
02:02:13,830 --> 02:02:14,900
What picture is this?

2674
02:02:14,900 --> 02:02:16,200
What is it trying to say?

2675
02:02:16,630 --> 02:02:19,100
The door is closed, she is sleeping,
and the time had changed to evening.

2676
02:02:19,100 --> 02:02:20,230
Except those, nothing had changed.

2677
02:02:20,230 --> 02:02:22,300
I checked the calendar too,
and it was the same.

2678
02:02:22,840 --> 02:02:24,200
Is it on the same day?

2679
02:02:26,440 --> 02:02:29,940
I tried to remember
as many details as possible.

2680
02:02:30,240 --> 02:02:32,480
I checked the overall context too,
of course,

2681
02:02:33,210 --> 02:02:35,050
but I tried to spot things out of place...

2682
02:02:35,050 --> 02:02:37,750
as if I was playing a picture puzzle.

2683
02:02:37,750 --> 02:02:42,020
I tried to remember
down to the angle of the lamp.

2684
02:02:42,020 --> 02:02:44,290
The kitchen utensils present...

2685
02:02:44,290 --> 02:02:47,530
and the bottles. There were
two bottles in the initial picture,

2686
02:02:47,530 --> 02:02:48,660
but only one was present in this picture.

2687
02:02:49,060 --> 02:02:51,870
And the sunlight was shining
onto the kitchen,

2688
02:02:51,870 --> 02:02:53,800
but for the three windows at the door,

2689
02:02:53,800 --> 02:02:57,000
it was colored dark blue like it's night.

2690
02:02:57,000 --> 02:03:00,310
That means it was blocked
by window films, perhaps.

2691
02:03:00,310 --> 02:03:04,910
This could be an important clue
to this case.

2692
02:03:15,620 --> 02:03:16,620
First,

2693
02:03:17,160 --> 02:03:19,290
I'll explain what's different
from that picture.

2694
02:03:19,290 --> 02:03:20,660
The door is closed,

2695
02:03:20,660 --> 02:03:21,860
and the entrance is closed.

2696
02:03:21,860 --> 02:03:23,360
And the entrance...

2697
02:03:23,360 --> 02:03:25,900
Here was colored dark blue.

2698
02:03:25,900 --> 02:03:27,170
I thought it was night,

2699
02:03:27,170 --> 02:03:28,640
but I think they're window films.

2700
02:03:28,640 --> 02:03:31,170
Because it had sunlight coming in
just like this picture.

2701
02:03:31,170 --> 02:03:32,440
- The kitchen at the back.
- Okay.

2702
02:03:32,440 --> 02:03:34,840
And the woman is sleeping alone.
She's alone.

2703
02:03:34,840 --> 02:03:36,510
And she had covered herself with a scarf.

2704
02:03:36,510 --> 02:03:39,050
- And this picture has two bottles.
- Bottles?

2705
02:03:39,050 --> 02:03:41,180
- There are two bottles in the kitchen.
- Yes.

2706
02:03:41,650 --> 02:03:42,780
That other picture has one.

2707
02:03:42,780 --> 02:03:45,090
- Line up now.
- Got it?

2708
02:03:45,490 --> 02:03:48,220
(The number of bottles
changed from 2 to 1?)

2709
02:03:48,220 --> 02:03:50,190
So when the woman woke up,

2710
02:03:50,190 --> 02:03:53,160
someone ran away to the backdoor.

2711
02:03:53,160 --> 02:03:55,800
I think the woman might've been cheating.

2712
02:03:55,800 --> 02:03:56,800
I think this is right.

2713
02:03:59,700 --> 02:04:00,700
For now...

2714
02:04:01,030 --> 02:04:02,040
Wait.

2715
02:04:02,540 --> 02:04:05,240
What were you going to ask? Hold on.

2716
02:04:06,110 --> 02:04:08,480
He said the windows were
blocked by something,

2717
02:04:08,480 --> 02:04:11,010
but I had no idea
what he was talking about.

2718
02:04:11,250 --> 02:04:13,410
Still, it sounds plausible,
so I said he should go and ask.

2719
02:04:13,410 --> 02:04:16,280
I think
Kyoung Hoon will be good at this game...

2720
02:04:16,280 --> 02:04:18,450
because his thought process
is very anomalous,

2721
02:04:18,450 --> 02:04:20,920
and he comes up with ideas
which others can't.

2722
02:04:21,390 --> 02:04:22,990
Since you saw the picture,

2723
02:04:22,990 --> 02:04:24,290
- you should go in and ask.
- Okay.

2724
02:04:24,790 --> 02:04:26,390
I thought this game was all about
getting the answer fast.

2725
02:04:26,390 --> 02:04:28,760
I was very confident about this game.

2726
02:04:28,760 --> 02:04:31,700
Some of us have played this game before,
so it would end in one hour.

2727
02:04:31,700 --> 02:04:34,800
I thought it would finish
before the third hint was revealed.

2728
02:04:34,800 --> 02:04:36,670
But things were going too slow,

2729
02:04:36,670 --> 02:04:40,740
