3247
02:26:53,440 --> 02:26:55,210
There were two people in the picture,

3248
02:26:55,210 --> 02:26:57,340
so I thought asking about an accomplice...

3249
02:26:57,340 --> 02:26:59,710
should come next.

3250
02:26:59,850 --> 02:27:03,150
Is the cause of Mark's death...

3251
02:27:03,150 --> 02:27:07,120
related to his partner?

3252
02:27:07,590 --> 02:27:09,020
Yes, that is correct.

3253
02:27:09,990 --> 02:27:12,530
(Team C's keywords status:
Basement, gas, thief, accomplice)

3254
02:27:12,530 --> 02:27:16,030
(The only team to find out
the "accomplice" keyword)

3255
02:27:17,100 --> 02:27:18,500
Hey.

3256
02:27:18,860 --> 02:27:21,170
Hey, this is huge.

3257
02:27:21,170 --> 02:27:24,400
He committed the crime with someone else.
Accomplice?

3258
02:27:24,400 --> 02:27:25,700
- Yes.
- There's an accomplice.

3259
02:27:25,700 --> 02:27:26,970
- There is?
- Yes.

3260
02:27:27,270 --> 02:27:29,580
- Be quiet!
- Okay. Continue quickly.

3261
02:27:29,610 --> 02:27:30,680
And...

3262
02:27:30,680 --> 02:27:33,410
the cause of his death
is related to the accomplice.

3263
02:27:35,250 --> 02:27:36,950
The answers were all yes.

3264
02:27:37,020 --> 02:27:40,150
That meant
we were going in the right direction.

3265
02:27:40,150 --> 02:27:42,590
So we started to get excited.

3266
02:27:42,690 --> 02:27:44,060
The most important things now...

3267
02:27:44,160 --> 02:27:45,990
are the "basement" keyword,

3268
02:27:45,990 --> 02:27:47,960
he went to steal,

3269
02:27:47,960 --> 02:27:49,860
and the existence of an accomplice.

3270
02:27:49,860 --> 02:27:51,930
He died because of something
related to the accomplice.

3271
02:27:52,830 --> 02:27:54,230
(Meanwhile, Team C has yet to figure out
the "gas" keyword.)

3272
02:27:54,230 --> 02:27:55,670
What to do?

3273
02:27:55,670 --> 02:27:57,400
We need to find that.

3274
02:27:58,140 --> 02:27:59,210
(Each team's keyword status)

3275
02:27:59,210 --> 02:28:00,410
(Basement: Teams P1, P2, P3, C, R)

3276
02:28:00,410 --> 02:28:01,570
(Gas: Teams P1, P3)

3277
02:28:01,570 --> 02:28:02,680
(Thief: Team C)

3278
02:28:02,680 --> 02:28:03,780
(Accomplice: Team C)

3279
02:28:05,710 --> 02:28:07,080
Seriously.

3280
02:28:07,380 --> 02:28:10,120
The hidden item will be revealed now.

3281
02:28:10,120 --> 02:28:11,150
- What?
- We can't buy it now.

3282
02:28:11,150 --> 02:28:13,190
The hidden item of Mystery Time...

3283
02:28:13,950 --> 02:28:15,890
is an extra hint ticket.

3284
02:28:15,890 --> 02:28:19,430
You'll get one hint
in the form of a sentence.

3285
02:28:19,960 --> 02:28:22,760
It's a sentence? That's pretty good.

3286
02:28:22,860 --> 02:28:24,460
The number of available tickets...

3287
02:28:24,760 --> 02:28:27,100
- is five.
- Each team can buy one.

3288
02:28:27,730 --> 02:28:29,670
Buy it!

3289
02:28:30,640 --> 02:28:31,970
Seung Yong, buy it!

3290
02:28:34,670 --> 02:28:37,010
Buy it
and work your brain inside the room.

3291
02:28:37,140 --> 02:28:38,810
I'll buy the hidden item.

3292
02:28:38,840 --> 02:28:42,110
For Team Rookie, 20,000 dollars
will be deducted from the team funds.

3293
02:28:42,380 --> 02:28:44,220
Here is the extra hint.

3294
02:28:44,220 --> 02:28:45,320
Thanks.

3295
02:28:47,250 --> 02:28:51,290
(Mark has been to
this house 10 years ago.)

3296
02:28:52,320 --> 02:28:56,130
"We've been going in the wrong direction."

3297
02:28:56,200 --> 02:28:57,860
That was when I realized that.

3298
02:28:57,960 --> 02:28:59,770
He didn't come to fix anything.

3299
02:28:59,770 --> 02:29:01,500
He came with a different goal in mind.

3300
02:29:01,500 --> 02:29:03,900
That was what I got from the hint.

3301
02:29:04,840 --> 02:29:05,940
Seung Yong, it's important.

3302
02:29:05,940 --> 02:29:07,370
- It's important, right?
- I wrote it on the left side.

3303
02:29:07,370 --> 02:29:08,970
I'll go check again quickly.

3304
02:29:09,310 --> 02:29:12,240
Beom went to see the second hint.

3305
02:29:12,240 --> 02:29:15,310
But I thought I should see it myself.

3306
02:29:16,350 --> 02:29:17,650
This is exhausting.

3307
02:29:23,460 --> 02:29:25,060
Can you spot anything?

3308
02:29:26,360 --> 02:29:28,790
From what I heard,

3309
02:29:29,030 --> 02:29:32,970
the picture was about fixing a copper pipe
in the basement.

3310
02:29:32,970 --> 02:29:34,130
But when I saw the picture myself,

3311
02:29:34,130 --> 02:29:35,500
it was nothing like that.

3312
02:29:35,500 --> 02:29:37,840
It wasn't even the basement.

3313
02:29:37,840 --> 02:29:41,840
It just looked like he had ordered
some tool boxes.

3314
02:29:42,070 --> 02:29:44,980
On the wall next to the desk,

3315
02:29:45,140 --> 02:29:47,380
there were floor plans.

3316
02:29:47,380 --> 02:29:49,950
I thought, "This isn't the basement."

3317
02:29:50,050 --> 02:29:52,950
"It's showing how Mark prepared..."

3318
02:29:53,650 --> 02:29:56,260
"to disguise himself as an electrician."

3319
02:29:56,260 --> 02:29:59,760
That was what I got from the hint.

3320
02:30:00,430 --> 02:30:02,760
We keep getting new information.

3321
02:30:02,760 --> 02:30:04,900
- It keeps getting more difficult.
- Exactly.

3322
02:30:05,260 --> 02:30:08,030
The keywords aren't something
we can think of ourselves.

3323
02:30:11,340 --> 02:30:12,810
Tell me a hint if you know any.

3324
02:30:12,810 --> 02:30:14,010
Others might not,

3325
02:30:14,010 --> 02:30:16,440
but you of all people should tell me.

3326
02:30:17,640 --> 02:30:19,510
- I'll think about it.
- Do you have a stronger bond with them...

3327
02:30:19,510 --> 02:30:20,750
or me?

3328
02:30:20,780 --> 02:30:22,950
I'll think about it.

3329
02:30:23,350 --> 02:30:25,150
I wasn't going to say this,

3330
02:30:25,150 --> 02:30:27,290
but how could you run away
without telling me the answer...

3331
02:30:27,290 --> 02:30:29,390
when I untied you
and was right next to you?

3332
02:30:29,390 --> 02:30:30,820
No, by then,

3333
02:30:30,820 --> 02:30:32,790
Yeon Cheong already knew the answer.

3334
02:30:33,060 --> 02:30:34,890
I mean, anyway,

3335
02:30:35,390 --> 02:30:36,460
I untied you.

3336
02:30:36,460 --> 02:30:38,700
- I really wanted to help you.
- And...

3337
02:30:38,700 --> 02:30:40,900
Xitsuh too. I untied you...

3338
02:30:40,900 --> 02:30:42,740
and two other men.

3339
02:30:42,740 --> 02:30:45,040
How could the whole team run away?

3340
02:30:45,170 --> 02:30:47,170
So I'm waiting for the chance
to get back at you.

3341
02:30:48,010 --> 02:30:50,740
If I end up playing the Deathmatch,
I'll choose you as the opponent.

3342
02:30:58,120 --> 02:31:01,020
The third image hint is revealed.

3343
02:31:01,020 --> 02:31:02,690
(The third Time Room opens.)

3344
02:31:04,220 --> 02:31:05,460
Darn it.

3345
02:31:05,460 --> 02:31:07,190
I shouldn't have volunteered. I'm screwed.

3346
02:31:09,760 --> 02:31:11,560
By then,

3347
02:31:11,560 --> 02:31:13,700
I was completely beat from running around.

3348
02:31:13,700 --> 02:31:15,270
I had a mental breakdown too.

3349
02:31:23,710 --> 02:31:26,150
(Dozens of Astronomically Expensive Jewels
Stolen From a Downtown Jeweler)

3350
02:31:26,150 --> 02:31:27,750
It was a newspaper article.

3351
02:31:27,750 --> 02:31:30,020
An unprecedented amount of jewels
has been stolen.

3352
02:31:30,020 --> 02:31:33,750
The owner was devastated,
and there were the police present.

3353
02:31:33,850 --> 02:31:36,890
It had the day and date written too.

3354
02:31:36,890 --> 02:31:39,290
Under it was an article...

3355
02:31:39,290 --> 02:31:41,230
about smartphones
becoming a thing nowadays.

3356
02:31:42,030 --> 02:31:45,000
I didn't think much about it.

3357
02:31:47,830 --> 02:31:49,800
Finally, we got a useful hint.

3358
02:31:49,970 --> 02:31:54,070
I intuitively thought
the article was telling us...

3359
02:31:54,070 --> 02:31:55,770
the background story of the incident.

3360
02:31:55,770 --> 02:31:57,380
Sixteenth, Wednesday.

3361
02:31:58,810 --> 02:32:03,520
And the jeweler was stolen the jewels
worth millions of dollars.

3362
02:32:03,520 --> 02:32:06,590
An article about that
had made the headline.

3363
02:32:06,590 --> 02:32:07,850
Below it was...

3364
02:32:07,850 --> 02:32:11,260
about how smartphones
are replacing books and newspapers,

3365
02:32:11,260 --> 02:32:12,560
how the scene in the subway had changed,

3366
02:32:12,560 --> 02:32:14,030
one-person household becoming popular,

3367
02:32:14,030 --> 02:32:15,630
camping equipment,

3368
02:32:15,630 --> 02:32:17,460
and other incidental news.

3369
02:32:17,860 --> 02:32:19,830
I stared at it for a long time
and thought hard.

3370
02:32:20,900 --> 02:32:25,440
Mark should definitely be involved
in the jewel burglary.

3371
02:32:25,440 --> 02:32:27,770
Are the articles about smartphones
and so on there...

3372
02:32:28,670 --> 02:32:29,840
to confuse us?

3373
02:32:29,840 --> 02:32:31,840
It's been so long
since smartphones have become a thing.

3374
02:32:31,840 --> 02:32:33,510
Why is the article covering that now?

3375
02:32:33,780 --> 02:32:36,380
For now,
I'm sure he's related to the jewels.

3376
02:32:36,580 --> 02:32:41,390
Is Mark related to the valuables burglary
in the newspaper?

3377
02:32:41,820 --> 02:32:43,090
Yes, that is correct.

3378
02:32:43,290 --> 02:32:45,760
Oh, and can I buy the hint?

3379
02:32:45,860 --> 02:32:48,260
- Will you buy the extra hint ticket?
- Yes.

3380
02:32:48,790 --> 02:32:50,800
Here is the extra hint.

3381
02:32:50,800 --> 02:32:51,900
(Mark has been to this house
10 years ago.)

3382
02:32:53,370 --> 02:32:56,140
"Mark has been to this house
ten years ago."

3383
02:32:56,240 --> 02:32:57,540
But hold on.

3384
02:32:57,600 --> 02:32:59,370
It's his first time meeting the client.

3385
02:32:59,400 --> 02:33:00,870
What's this now?

3386
02:33:01,510 --> 02:33:03,510
"Mark has been to this house
ten years ago."

3387
02:33:03,540 --> 02:33:05,180
- Or...
- Ten years ago.

3388
02:33:05,180 --> 02:33:07,480
It's even harder
to fit that into the plot.

3389
02:33:07,510 --> 02:33:09,050
- It got harder with the hint.
- Yes.

3390
02:33:09,350 --> 02:33:12,550
He either lived in that house
in the past...

3391
02:33:12,920 --> 02:33:15,420
or he hid something in there.

3392
02:33:15,520 --> 02:33:17,260
That was a big hint.

3393
02:33:17,360 --> 02:33:19,020
Jewels? I see.

3394
02:33:19,020 --> 02:33:22,900
"Did he go there to take something?"
We should ask this.

3395
02:33:22,930 --> 02:33:25,430
Yes, I thought that too.

3396
02:33:25,530 --> 02:33:27,430
- Because...
- That could be it.

3397
02:33:27,730 --> 02:33:30,270
- Because...
- This is it.

3398
02:33:30,270 --> 02:33:31,740
- This could be it.
- Yes.

3399
02:33:33,070 --> 02:33:34,810
- Hold on. But...
- But...

3400
02:33:34,810 --> 02:33:36,070
this is recent news.

3401
02:33:36,070 --> 02:33:38,840
No, it's the news from the past.

3402
02:33:38,940 --> 02:33:40,410
It's a newspaper from the past.

3403
02:33:40,410 --> 02:33:42,410
He stole the jewels
and hid them in this house,

3404
02:33:42,410 --> 02:33:44,620
- so he went in to take them back.
- Yes.

3405
02:33:44,750 --> 02:33:45,850
- I...
- I think you're right.

3406
02:33:45,850 --> 02:33:48,320
The article is from the past,
come to think of it.

3407
02:33:48,320 --> 02:33:49,590
You're right.

3408
02:33:49,590 --> 02:33:51,560
I think the year was quite dated.

3409
02:33:51,560 --> 02:33:52,790
Okay.

3410
02:33:52,990 --> 02:33:55,560
He must've hidden the jewels. That was...

3411
02:33:55,560 --> 02:33:57,200
practically an established fact to us.

3412
02:33:57,460 --> 02:33:59,770
But he'd never met the woman before.

3413
02:33:59,830 --> 02:34:02,400
Did he use to live in the house, then?

3414
02:34:02,570 --> 02:34:03,870
We wrapped our hands around our heads.

3415
02:34:10,810 --> 02:34:12,210
I'll ask questions.

3416
02:34:12,510 --> 02:34:17,120
Are the jewels, which Mark went
to steal from the client's house,

3417
02:34:17,720 --> 02:34:23,760
the same jewels Mark hid ten years ago?

3418
02:34:24,990 --> 02:34:26,120
(Tae Gyun checked the third image hint.)

3419
02:34:26,120 --> 02:34:28,560
October 16, Wednesday.

3420
02:34:29,160 --> 02:34:30,760
Seriously...

3421
02:34:31,460 --> 02:34:32,630
A jewel burglar?

3422
02:34:32,630 --> 02:34:33,770
Right.

3423
02:34:34,730 --> 02:34:37,200
He must've gone to the basement
to steal the jewels.

3424
02:34:37,570 --> 02:34:40,810
(He purchases the extra hint ticket too.)

3425
02:34:44,410 --> 02:34:46,950
He's been to the house ten years ago,

3426
02:34:46,950 --> 02:34:48,410
but he's never seen the client before.

3427
02:34:50,250 --> 02:34:52,520
If it was ten years ago,

3428
02:34:53,390 --> 02:34:54,690
that house...

3429
02:34:55,350 --> 02:34:56,860
It would've had a different owner.

3430
02:34:56,860 --> 02:34:58,660
There's a high chance
it had a different owner back then.

3431
02:34:59,220 --> 02:35:02,090
Then he hid the jewels
he stole ten years ago here...

3432
02:35:02,090 --> 02:35:05,000
and went to take them back. Right?

3433
02:35:05,800 --> 02:35:11,900
Are they the same jewels
as the ones Mark hid ten years ago?

3434
02:35:13,510 --> 02:35:15,070
Yes, that is correct.

3435
02:35:15,910 --> 02:35:16,980
But wait.

3436
02:35:16,980 --> 02:35:19,340
I have no idea
what the third-party involvement is about.

3437
02:35:19,340 --> 02:35:21,050
When we asked questions in the beginning,

3438
02:35:21,050 --> 02:35:24,020
we found out there was a third party
who was involved in this case.

3439
02:35:24,020 --> 02:35:25,420
Who is the third party?

3440
02:35:25,420 --> 02:35:27,790
So I asked if there was an accomplice.

3441
02:35:27,990 --> 02:35:30,090
Did Mark have an accomplice?

3442
02:35:30,820 --> 02:35:32,460
Yes, that is correct.

3443
02:35:34,530 --> 02:35:36,630
He had an accomplice. Then...

3444
02:35:36,800 --> 02:35:38,400
how, and in what way,

3445
02:35:38,400 --> 02:35:40,470
did he inhale the gas accidentally?

3446
02:35:40,600 --> 02:35:43,470
We couldn't find
the answer to that question.

3447
02:35:43,540 --> 02:35:44,840
No, I think...

3448
02:35:44,840 --> 02:35:46,710
If the woman isn't a thief...

3449
02:35:46,770 --> 02:35:48,210
and Mark visited the house more than once,

3450
02:35:48,570 --> 02:35:51,980
it means Mark stole the jewels...

3451
02:35:51,980 --> 02:35:54,780
and hid them in that house.

3452
02:35:54,950 --> 02:35:56,450
That could be it.

3453
02:35:56,950 --> 02:35:57,950
That could be it.

3454
02:35:57,950 --> 02:36:00,020
So he came back to take them back.

3455
02:36:00,090 --> 02:36:02,290
But he died while trying.

3456
02:36:02,390 --> 02:36:04,190
Then I'll try to come up with
the questions.

3457
02:36:04,190 --> 02:36:05,690
That makes sense.

3458
02:36:06,220 --> 02:36:07,890
- I'll sort them out.
- You get what I mean, right?

3459
02:36:07,890 --> 02:36:09,630
Yes, I got it. You should think about...

3460
02:36:09,630 --> 02:36:11,460
- the cause of death.
- Okay.

3461
02:36:11,660 --> 02:36:14,230
The accomplice is related to this case.

3462
02:36:14,230 --> 02:36:16,030
We need to provide the reason anyway.

3463
02:36:16,030 --> 02:36:19,300
I think the accomplice killed Mark
because they thought he was the woman.

3464
02:36:19,300 --> 02:36:20,510
Then...

3465
02:36:20,640 --> 02:36:22,470
Will you ask about suffocation?

3466
02:36:23,580 --> 02:36:25,180
- Suffocation.
- Sounds good.

3467
02:36:25,610 --> 02:36:27,580
I have an idea.

3468
02:36:27,580 --> 02:36:28,780
Go on.

3469
02:36:28,780 --> 02:36:29,880
Let's ask this.

3470
02:36:29,980 --> 02:36:31,580
"Did the accomplice kill him
by an accident?"

3471
02:36:31,980 --> 02:36:33,520
We need to find the cause of the accident.

3472
02:36:33,520 --> 02:36:34,890
- Exactly, suffocation...
- The cause of the accident.

3473
02:36:34,890 --> 02:36:37,220
- We need to find that from here.
- Yes.

3474
02:36:37,320 --> 02:36:38,960
But let's say this is wrong.

3475
02:36:38,960 --> 02:36:40,890
If it's wrong,
we'll think about the next step then.

3476
02:36:40,890 --> 02:36:42,060
But if we don't ask,

3477
02:36:42,060 --> 02:36:44,130
we can't fill up this gigantic hole.

3478
02:36:44,930 --> 02:36:46,600
Let's ask other questions first...

3479
02:36:46,600 --> 02:36:47,930
and ask that last.

3480
02:36:54,240 --> 02:36:59,910
Did Mark go to the client's house...

3481
02:36:59,910 --> 02:37:02,010
to take back the jewels he had stolen?

3482
02:37:02,750 --> 02:37:04,280
Yes, that is correct.

3483
02:37:05,350 --> 02:37:06,820
Did the accomplice...

3484
02:37:07,250 --> 02:37:12,220
accidentally lead Mark to his death?

3485
02:37:12,820 --> 02:37:14,660
No, that is incorrect.

3486
02:37:21,030 --> 02:37:23,200
What other causes are left
for someone to die accidentally?

3487
02:37:23,200 --> 02:37:24,570
That was the question.

3488
02:37:24,570 --> 02:37:27,040
So I suggested suffocation.

3489
02:37:27,040 --> 02:37:28,710
- Let's try this.
- Suffocation?

3490
02:37:28,710 --> 02:37:30,980
- Yes, let's try this. And...
- Okay.

3491
02:37:30,980 --> 02:37:32,040
And...

3492
02:37:32,040 --> 02:37:33,380
But...

3493
02:37:33,380 --> 02:37:35,380
it can't be suffocation.

3494
02:37:35,550 --> 02:37:37,920
I asked if the accomplice
directly led him to his death,

3495
02:37:37,920 --> 02:37:39,220
and the answer was no.

3496
02:37:42,920 --> 02:37:44,060
This is so annoying.

3497
02:37:44,390 --> 02:37:46,990
The questions I wanted to ask
kept being ignored.

3498
02:37:47,130 --> 02:37:49,260
- This is why I'm breaking down.
- Okay.

3499
02:37:50,000 --> 02:37:52,600
When we went through 2 to 3 rounds,

3500
02:37:53,200 --> 02:37:55,730
there were many chances
