3754
02:49:05,000 --> 02:49:07,440
Mark killed his accomplice...

3755
02:49:07,740 --> 02:49:11,110
and went to the basement floor
of the accomplice's house.

3756
02:49:11,110 --> 02:49:14,410
He buried the dead body of the accomplice
along with the jewelry.

3757
02:49:14,910 --> 02:49:19,150
Ten years later, he went back
to that same house with a new owner...

3758
02:49:19,150 --> 02:49:21,590
to retrieve the jewelry.

3759
02:49:21,690 --> 02:49:23,650
As Mark tried to get out the jewelry,

3760
02:49:23,890 --> 02:49:27,160
he died of suffocation...

3761
02:49:27,160 --> 02:49:29,330
after breathing in the poisonous gas
from the dead body.

3762
02:49:30,760 --> 02:49:32,000
That's the right answer.

3763
02:49:33,130 --> 02:49:35,670
The timer will stop for all teams.

3764
02:49:36,970 --> 02:49:39,840
I didn't expect myself to scream.

3765
02:49:40,000 --> 02:49:42,270
Gosh.

3766
02:49:43,340 --> 02:49:45,040
I felt elated.

3767
02:49:45,040 --> 02:49:47,040
I went out, and we put our arms
around each other.

3768
02:49:47,040 --> 02:49:50,380
It felt like I scored a goal
at a soccer tournament.

3769
02:49:50,380 --> 02:49:51,920
I felt so excited.

3770
02:49:52,480 --> 02:49:55,520
In a flash, I felt a thrill rush up...

3771
02:49:55,520 --> 02:49:57,190
from the end of my toes
to the end of my head.

3772
02:49:57,190 --> 02:49:58,360
We all went wild.

3773
02:49:58,360 --> 02:50:00,290
We all put our arms around each other.

3774
02:50:01,560 --> 02:50:03,900
Things worked out for us in the end.

3775
02:50:03,960 --> 02:50:06,360
Our team synergy came together...

3776
02:50:06,360 --> 02:50:07,570
and it felt nice.

3777
02:50:08,430 --> 02:50:10,400
Round One comes to an end...

3778
02:50:10,400 --> 02:50:12,400
after Team P3 gets the right answer.

3779
02:50:12,440 --> 02:50:13,640
- Nice job.
- Gosh!

3780
02:50:13,940 --> 02:50:16,940
This is the whole story
of the case of Round One.

3781
02:50:19,040 --> 02:50:23,480
Mark was a thief who stole
expensive jewels around ten years ago.

3782
02:50:24,480 --> 02:50:27,290
After an argument with his fellow thief
based on the jewelry distribution,

3783
02:50:27,290 --> 02:50:28,590
he ended up killing him.

3784
02:50:28,590 --> 02:50:31,060
He wrapped the dead body and the jewelry
with a plastic bag...

3785
02:50:31,060 --> 02:50:33,820
and hid it inside the wall in the basement
of his accomplice's house.

3786
02:50:35,190 --> 02:50:38,930
Mark was locked up in prison
after getting caught by the police.

3787
02:50:39,360 --> 02:50:42,730
Meanwhile, the accomplice's house
was sold to another owner.

3788
02:50:43,000 --> 02:50:45,240
It was all based on deduction.

3789
02:50:45,500 --> 02:50:48,010
After being released, Mark disguised
himself as an electrician...

3790
02:50:48,010 --> 02:50:50,240
and returned to that house.

3791
02:50:50,980 --> 02:50:52,580
When the owner of the house fell asleep,

3792
02:50:52,580 --> 02:50:55,350
he closed the basement door
and knocked down the wall.

3793
02:50:56,780 --> 02:50:59,020
That was way off.

3794
02:50:59,580 --> 02:51:02,350
After opening the plastic bag
that was closed for ten years,

3795
02:51:02,450 --> 02:51:04,990
the poisonous gas from the dead body
came out.

3796
02:51:06,220 --> 02:51:09,190
Mark ended up dying by suffocation
in the basement...

3797
02:51:09,190 --> 02:51:11,260
that lacked ventilation.

3798
02:51:12,730 --> 02:51:14,830
This is really tough.

3799
02:51:15,900 --> 02:51:17,700
It's really tough.

3800
02:51:18,200 --> 02:51:19,940
Our hard work was worth it.

3801
02:51:20,070 --> 02:51:22,010
- It's a relief we placed first.
- Right.

3802
02:51:23,170 --> 02:51:24,780
- Hye Seon did a great job toward the end.
- Gosh.

3803
02:51:25,510 --> 02:51:29,680
The members of Team P3 may return
to their room and wait.

3804
02:51:30,410 --> 02:51:31,580
Let's go.

3805
02:51:31,650 --> 02:51:32,920
I'm sorry for leaving first.

3806
02:51:32,920 --> 02:51:34,290
I should have a cigarette
to celebrate this joyful moment.

3807
02:51:34,290 --> 02:51:35,450
Gosh, the sun is up.

3808
02:51:36,590 --> 02:51:39,320
The accumulated time
of Round One will be revealed.

3809
02:51:40,390 --> 02:51:41,590
Team P1.

3810
02:51:41,590 --> 02:51:42,890
(Jeong Keun Woo: 4:49:22,
Lee Sang Min: 5:04:18,)

3811
02:51:42,890 --> 02:51:44,260
(Park Ji Min: 5:16:40,
Lee Tae Gyun: 5:45:30)

3812
02:51:44,500 --> 02:51:45,760
Team P2.

3813
02:51:45,760 --> 02:51:47,000
(Ha Seung Jin: 4:55:18,
Lee Jin Hyeong: 4:58:30,)

3814
02:51:47,000 --> 02:51:48,130
(YunB: 5:04:42, Hyun Sung Joo: 5:14:26)

3815
02:51:48,330 --> 02:51:49,670
Team Challenger.

3816
02:51:49,670 --> 02:51:50,900
(Kim Nam Hee: 4:53:18,
Kim You Hyun: 5:01:18,)

3817
02:51:50,900 --> 02:51:52,100
(Kim Kyoung Hoon: 5:10:08,
Kang Ji Hoo: 5:21:18)

3818
02:51:52,200 --> 02:51:53,540
Team Rookie.

3819
02:51:53,540 --> 02:51:55,040
(Lee Gwan Hee: 4:56:18,
Kwak Beom: 4:58:20,)

3820
02:51:55,040 --> 02:51:56,510
(Shin Seung Yong: 5:12:38)

3821
02:51:56,870 --> 02:52:00,950
Soon,
Round Two of Mystery Time will begin.

3822
02:52:01,810 --> 02:52:04,350
I have a suggestion.

3823
02:52:04,350 --> 02:52:06,580
How does it sound
to take turns by each team...

3824
02:52:06,580 --> 02:52:09,020
instead of lining up?

3825
02:52:09,020 --> 02:52:10,250
- I think that's a good idea.
- Right.

3826
02:52:10,250 --> 02:52:11,390
The line gets too congested.

3827
02:52:11,390 --> 02:52:12,660
We'll all wait for our turns.

3828
02:52:12,660 --> 02:52:13,890
(They agree to take turns by each team.)

3829
02:52:13,890 --> 02:52:17,260
This was the first thing we mentioned
after the end of Round One.

3830
02:52:17,260 --> 02:52:18,500
"Let's take turns."

3831
02:52:18,900 --> 02:52:21,730
There was a suggestion
that this would be much better.

3832
02:52:21,730 --> 02:52:24,070
All teams agreed...

3833
02:52:24,070 --> 02:52:25,340
to set an order...

3834
02:52:25,340 --> 02:52:26,640
and take turns.

3835
02:52:26,640 --> 02:52:27,640
Hey, Jin Hyeong.

3836
02:52:27,640 --> 02:52:32,780
In Round 2, you either place 1st,
2nd and 3rd, or 4th.

3837
02:52:32,780 --> 02:52:34,180
- Placing fourth is the worst.
- Right.

3838
02:52:34,180 --> 02:52:35,880
Fourth place heads to
the Deathmatch no matter what.

3839
02:52:35,880 --> 02:52:37,210
- You want to team up with us?
- No.

3840
02:52:37,210 --> 02:52:38,820
I'm not asking to team up
right from the start.

3841
02:52:39,380 --> 02:52:41,150
If both of our teams fail...

3842
02:52:41,150 --> 02:52:43,820
and 1 of those 2 teams
manage to get the answer 1st,

3843
02:52:43,920 --> 02:52:45,620
that is when we want to place 2nd or 3rd.

3844
02:52:45,620 --> 02:52:47,260
- We want to avoid placing last?
- Right.

3845
02:52:47,660 --> 02:52:50,190
Are you willing to team up
to avoid placing last?

3846
02:52:50,190 --> 02:52:51,260
Of course.

3847
02:52:51,260 --> 02:52:53,860
If the team in 1st place
gets decided in Round 2,

3848
02:52:54,030 --> 02:52:55,400
the teams in 2nd and 3rd place...

3849
02:52:55,400 --> 02:52:57,500
must pick
one elimination candidate each...

3850
02:52:57,500 --> 02:52:58,870
through a vote.

3851
02:52:58,970 --> 02:53:00,200
The team in last place...

3852
02:53:00,200 --> 02:53:02,270
automatically gets one person
to become an elimination candidate.

3853
02:53:02,440 --> 02:53:03,670
Thus,

3854
02:53:03,810 --> 02:53:07,140
when 1 team secures 1st place in Round 2,

3855
02:53:07,380 --> 02:53:09,650
two teams out of the other three
can team up.

3856
02:53:09,650 --> 02:53:11,980
The teams in 2nd and 3rd place
are in the same position in Round 2.

3857
02:53:12,950 --> 02:53:15,820
That was why I talked about this
with Jin Hyeong who was next to me.

3858
02:53:15,820 --> 02:53:18,920
I said that we should team up
if we need to.

3859
02:53:19,260 --> 02:53:20,990
- What should we do in Round Two?
- But...

3860
02:53:20,990 --> 02:53:23,090
I already talked with Jin Hyeong.

3861
02:53:23,090 --> 02:53:25,360
I think they're not good at this game.

3862
02:53:25,660 --> 02:53:26,730
- Team P2?
- Yes.

3863
02:53:27,470 --> 02:53:30,230
But I think...

3864
02:53:30,230 --> 02:53:31,640
Team Rookie is the worst.

3865
02:53:31,970 --> 02:53:33,940
- That's true, but...
- They can't seem to follow along.

3866
02:53:33,940 --> 02:53:36,110
That's true about them.

3867
02:53:36,470 --> 02:53:38,440
Keeping the easier team alive...

3868
02:53:38,440 --> 02:53:41,050
- might favor us in the long term.
- Right.

3869
02:53:41,050 --> 02:53:43,550
But will we get anything
by sharing information with them?

3870
02:53:44,080 --> 02:53:45,880
It's better to team up with Team Rookie.

3871
02:53:46,450 --> 02:53:47,750
Sang Min and Keun Woo...

3872
02:53:47,750 --> 02:53:49,490
couldn't trust Jin Hyeong.

3873
02:53:49,490 --> 02:53:51,820
That was why they felt reluctant
to team up with Team P2.

3874
02:53:52,160 --> 02:53:53,860
They wanted to team up
with Team R instead.

3875
02:53:53,960 --> 02:53:55,990
Hey, Gwan Hee. If we end up...

3876
02:53:55,990 --> 02:53:59,160
- having to team up with each other,
- Right.

3877
02:53:59,160 --> 02:54:01,830
we are considering your team
the highest priority.

3878
02:54:01,830 --> 02:54:05,440
When either Team P2 or Team C
take 1st place in Round 2,

3879
02:54:05,440 --> 02:54:06,640
Right.

3880
02:54:06,640 --> 02:54:09,810
- we can share information.
- Right.

3881
02:54:09,810 --> 02:54:11,180
I understand what you're saying.

3882
02:54:11,180 --> 02:54:12,440
- Let's work together.
- Then,

3883
02:54:12,440 --> 02:54:14,010
when the team in first place...

3884
02:54:14,010 --> 02:54:15,350
- gets decided in Round Two,
- Right.

3885
02:54:15,350 --> 02:54:17,980
- we can exchange the things we know...
- Right.

3886
02:54:17,980 --> 02:54:19,220
- with each other.
- Right.

3887
02:54:19,220 --> 02:54:20,920
Well,

3888
02:54:20,920 --> 02:54:22,420
we don't know...

3889
02:54:22,420 --> 02:54:24,990
how the Deathmatch candidates
will be decided,

3890
02:54:24,990 --> 02:54:27,560
but we'll do our best to help each other
through the votes.

3891
02:54:27,560 --> 02:54:30,160
When both of our teams
fail to place first,

3892
02:54:30,260 --> 02:54:31,630
we asked if they were willing
to team up with us.

3893
02:54:32,030 --> 02:54:33,560
Team R accepted our offer.

3894
02:54:33,960 --> 02:54:35,870
- Jin Hyeong, can I have a word?
- Yes?

3895
02:54:35,870 --> 02:54:37,400
What? Why?

3896
02:54:38,000 --> 02:54:39,270
- I talked with you yesterday.
- Right.

3897
02:54:39,270 --> 02:54:42,540
The two of us...

3898
02:54:42,540 --> 02:54:45,640
- have a bond with each other.
- Right.

3899
02:54:45,640 --> 02:54:47,240
You decided to team up
with Team Challenger, right?

3900
02:54:47,710 --> 02:54:50,780
Jin Hyeong said to me, "You decided to
team up with Team C, right?"

3901
02:54:50,780 --> 02:54:52,220
I've never...

3902
02:54:52,220 --> 02:54:54,120
talked with Team C at all.

3903
02:54:54,120 --> 02:54:56,820
I wondered
where he had heard of this strange rumor.

3904
02:54:56,820 --> 02:55:00,060
I told him that we weren't going to
team up with them.

3905
02:55:00,260 --> 02:55:01,560
We're going to team up with Team Rookie.

3906
02:55:01,560 --> 02:55:03,730
- Never mind.
- I was going to tell you this.

3907
02:55:03,730 --> 02:55:05,300
- Let's freely part ways.
- Okay.

3908
02:55:05,830 --> 02:55:06,860
Jin Hyeong said,

3909
02:55:06,860 --> 02:55:09,130
"Things worked out.
We decided to team up with Team R,"

3910
02:55:09,130 --> 02:55:10,270
"so we can't work with you."

3911
02:55:10,670 --> 02:55:12,070
I thought to myself, "What is he saying?"

3912
02:55:12,240 --> 02:55:14,840
"Team R decided to team up with us."

3913
02:55:14,840 --> 02:55:16,510
That was why I decided to meet up
with Gwan Hee in the main hall.

3914
02:55:22,110 --> 02:55:24,180
- Gwan Hee.
- It's right here.

3915
02:55:24,280 --> 02:55:26,180
Well,

3916
02:55:26,180 --> 02:55:29,150
someone said that we were
going to team up with Team C.

3917
02:55:29,150 --> 02:55:30,650
Who was it?

3918
02:55:30,990 --> 02:55:32,620
Actually, Team P2...

3919
02:55:32,620 --> 02:55:34,020
- asked to team up with us.
- Right.

3920
02:55:34,020 --> 02:55:35,560
I think we have to team up with them.

3921
02:55:35,560 --> 02:55:37,260
You're going to team up with them? Not us?

3922
02:55:37,530 --> 02:55:39,260
I heard that your team
already decided to...

3923
02:55:39,260 --> 02:55:40,830
team up with Team Challenger.

3924
02:55:41,400 --> 02:55:43,470
We didn't get in touch
with Team Challenger at all.

3925
02:55:45,940 --> 02:55:50,740
I wondered why
Team P2 asked to team up with us...

3926
02:55:51,480 --> 02:55:53,010
with false information.

3927
02:55:53,310 --> 02:55:54,950
I thought about who would...

3928
02:55:54,950 --> 02:55:57,720
cunningly use this false information,

3929
02:55:57,720 --> 02:55:59,280
and Jin Hyeong was the only one
who came to mind.

3930
02:56:08,130 --> 02:56:09,530
After Round One,

3931
02:56:09,530 --> 02:56:12,100
Team P1's Tae Gyun made an offer
to team up with us.

3932
02:56:12,100 --> 02:56:15,200
"Let's team up with each other
and help each other in the game."

3933
02:56:15,200 --> 02:56:17,230
After that, Team Rookie...

3934
02:56:17,230 --> 02:56:19,200
made the same offer.

3935
02:56:19,200 --> 02:56:22,170
"Let's work with each other
until the end of Round Two."

3936
02:56:22,170 --> 02:56:24,880
They even mentioned helping each other...

3937
02:56:24,980 --> 02:56:26,310
with our votes.

3938
02:56:26,740 --> 02:56:28,050
(Team P2 and Team R
are sitting together after Round 1.)

3939
02:56:28,050 --> 02:56:31,020
Would there be teams that team up
for Round Two?

3940
02:56:31,020 --> 02:56:33,420
- To be able to place second,
- I don't think so.

3941
02:56:34,180 --> 02:56:35,390
I think we should be quick to act.

3942
02:56:35,390 --> 02:56:37,290
If it's a matter of deciding
who places 3rd or 4th,

3943
02:56:37,290 --> 02:56:40,460
I believe it will definitely be good
to team up.

3944
02:56:40,460 --> 02:56:42,760
- Right.
- I think it will be hard to decide...

3945
02:56:42,760 --> 02:56:45,430
who should place second.

3946
02:56:45,430 --> 02:56:46,630
The best thing...

3947
02:56:46,630 --> 02:56:48,100
when teaming up with another team...

3948
02:56:48,200 --> 02:56:50,830
is to have a mindset that
it doesn't matter who places second.

3949
02:56:51,000 --> 02:56:53,000
If one team secures a position,

3950
02:56:53,000 --> 02:56:55,770
more money can be given to the team...

3951
02:56:55,770 --> 02:56:58,380
that places 3rd or 4th.

3952
02:56:58,480 --> 02:57:00,680
As we're shorter in number,

3953
02:57:00,680 --> 02:57:02,780
we are willing to accept any offers...

3954
02:57:02,780 --> 02:57:05,920
from those higher in number.

3955
02:57:06,950 --> 02:57:09,090
- Gwan Hee is my junior!
- Right.

3956
02:57:09,090 --> 02:57:11,090
- There's already a bond.
- Right.

3957
02:57:11,360 --> 02:57:12,920
- It's an oath of brotherhood.
- Right.

3958
02:57:13,220 --> 02:57:14,660
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

3959
02:57:14,660 --> 02:57:16,330
(Team P2 and Team R
decided to team up first.)

3960
02:57:16,330 --> 02:57:18,430
That was how we decided
to team up with Team Rookie.

3961
02:57:18,430 --> 02:57:21,330
But Tae Gyun came down...

3962
02:57:21,330 --> 02:57:22,530
and told me that he talked
with his teammates...

3963
02:57:22,530 --> 02:57:24,130
and that they decided
they could team up with us.

3964
02:57:24,300 --> 02:57:26,000
If they can't team up with us,

3965
02:57:26,000 --> 02:57:28,910
Tae Gyun definitely must've tried to
team up with another team.

3966
02:57:28,910 --> 02:57:30,740
They won't team up with us.

3967
02:57:30,770 --> 02:57:32,580
Team Rookie will team up with us.

3968
02:57:32,740 --> 02:57:34,550
That means there's only one team left.

3969
02:57:34,550 --> 02:57:35,910
Team Challenger.

3970
02:57:36,050 --> 02:57:37,850
That was why I thought Team P1...

3971
02:57:37,850 --> 02:57:39,920
decided to team up with Team Challenger.

3972
02:57:41,790 --> 02:57:43,520
This is what I mean.

3973
02:57:43,850 --> 02:57:44,990
Did you hear...

3974
02:57:44,990 --> 02:57:47,090
that Team Challenger and Team P1
decided to team up?

3975
02:57:47,220 --> 02:57:48,230
Team Challenger and Team P1?

3976
02:57:48,230 --> 02:57:49,230
They decided to team up like us.

3977
02:57:49,230 --> 02:57:50,390
- Really?
- Yes.

3978
02:57:50,760 --> 02:57:52,330
I don't think
we have to try to read the room.

3979
02:57:52,330 --> 02:57:54,530
We all know what's going on.

3980
02:57:55,100 --> 02:57:57,100
(Torn)

3981
02:57:59,440 --> 02:58:01,770
I heard that Team Challenger and Team P1
decided to team up.

3982
02:58:03,810 --> 02:58:05,140
Darn it.

3983
02:58:06,040 --> 02:58:08,450
We have to be clear
with what we're going to do.

3984
02:58:09,510 --> 02:58:10,750
We have no choice but to go with Team P2.

3985
02:58:10,750 --> 02:58:12,250
- Right.
- We have to go with Team P2.

3986
02:58:12,320 --> 02:58:15,920
Tae Gyun's team also made an offer
to team up.

3987
02:58:15,920 --> 02:58:18,060
Other than Tae Gyun,

3988
02:58:18,060 --> 02:58:19,790
there were Sang Min,

3989
02:58:19,790 --> 02:58:22,230
Keun Woo, and Ji Min...

3990
02:58:22,230 --> 02:58:24,060
and I thought they weren't very good
at the game.

3991
02:58:24,060 --> 02:58:26,700
Instead of Team P1 with just Tae Gyun,

3992
02:58:26,700 --> 02:58:29,230
I thought Seung Jin's team was better...

3993
02:58:29,230 --> 02:58:31,240
with Jin Hyeong and Sung Joo.

3994
02:58:31,240 --> 02:58:32,540
That was the reason
for choosing that team.

3995
