03:32:47,020 --> 03:32:48,690
- Will you ask a question?
- Yes.

4751
03:32:49,590 --> 03:32:52,560
If it was to prevent a major loss,

4752
03:32:52,830 --> 03:32:54,000
was it for cash?

4753
03:32:57,700 --> 03:32:59,630
I think this is...

4754
03:33:00,540 --> 03:33:02,300
- an important clue.
- What?

4755
03:33:02,900 --> 03:33:04,540
When I was in the room,

4756
03:33:04,540 --> 03:33:06,170
the second hint about a loss was revealed.

4757
03:33:06,480 --> 03:33:09,850
After hearing that it was about a loss,

4758
03:33:09,850 --> 03:33:13,820
I asked if it was for cash.

4759
03:33:14,080 --> 03:33:16,790
That includes transfers between accounts.

4760
03:33:17,150 --> 03:33:18,920
That could be considered cash.

4761
03:33:19,150 --> 03:33:20,790
- Yes, that is correct.
- Sorry?

4762
03:33:20,790 --> 03:33:23,390
Is the cash kept somewhere?

4763
03:33:23,630 --> 03:33:24,990
It is not important.

4764
03:33:25,260 --> 03:33:26,500
It is not important.

4765
03:33:26,700 --> 03:33:28,960
For the last question, I asked...

4766
03:33:29,260 --> 03:33:32,300
Is the loss strictly in cash,

4767
03:33:32,300 --> 03:33:33,740
excluding real estate and stocks?

4768
03:33:34,040 --> 03:33:36,100
- Only in cash?
- What's the answer?

4769
03:33:36,540 --> 03:33:37,540
Yes, that is correct.

4770
03:33:37,540 --> 03:33:38,640
- It's only in cash?
- Yes.

4771
03:33:38,640 --> 03:33:41,640
- It's not about stocks.
- No. It's only in cash.

4772
03:33:42,140 --> 03:33:43,650
Did you ask...

4773
03:33:43,650 --> 03:33:45,580
if the CEO was involved
in something illegal?

4774
03:33:45,580 --> 03:33:46,720
You've never asked, right?

4775
03:33:46,880 --> 03:33:48,380
It could be about drugs.

4776
03:33:48,720 --> 03:33:50,350
The actor found out something.

4777
03:33:50,350 --> 03:33:52,050
- Corruption.
- Yes, he found out the CEO's corruption.

4778
03:33:52,050 --> 03:33:54,890
Maybe they were pressed for that.
"You should turn yourself in."

4779
03:33:55,490 --> 03:33:57,660
- "Otherwise, I will..."
- "I'll expose it."

4780
03:33:57,660 --> 03:33:59,030
"expose it." That's what he said.

4781
03:33:59,160 --> 03:34:01,000
- That's why they were pressed for time.
- The question...

4782
03:34:01,000 --> 03:34:02,330
Yes, we should ask that.

4783
03:34:02,500 --> 03:34:05,500
I wondered what we couldn't solve
when we'd made it thus far.

4784
03:34:05,600 --> 03:34:08,740
We were almost there.
We just needed the first sentence.

4785
03:34:09,300 --> 03:34:12,470
(Meanwhile, Team Challenger hasn't found
a keyword related to the culprit.)

4786
03:34:12,840 --> 03:34:14,280
- Right!
- What?

4787
03:34:14,380 --> 03:34:17,550
The stuntman was a stand-in for the movie.

4788
03:34:17,580 --> 03:34:21,120
But that's actually an ad.

4789
03:34:21,520 --> 03:34:22,920
Maybe the PPL company killed him,

4790
03:34:22,920 --> 03:34:24,320
not the film production company.

4791
03:34:24,720 --> 03:34:26,420
There is a penalty clause
in PPL agreements.

4792
03:34:26,420 --> 03:34:29,860
If the actor gets hurt or dies,

4793
03:34:29,860 --> 03:34:31,360
they must pay the penalty.

4794
03:34:31,430 --> 03:34:32,990
That's why they killed him.

4795
03:34:33,360 --> 03:34:34,900
They killed him for the penalty payout.

4796
03:34:34,900 --> 03:34:37,130
And the termination date
for the agreement was approaching.

4797
03:34:37,400 --> 03:34:38,600
- Wait.
- Hold on.

4798
03:34:38,600 --> 03:34:39,700
That makes sense,

4799
03:34:39,700 --> 03:34:42,140
but it's not PPL.

4800
03:34:42,140 --> 03:34:44,070
The agency of the actor...

4801
03:34:44,910 --> 03:34:46,140
If the actor gets hurt...

4802
03:34:46,140 --> 03:34:47,740
Right. Within the agreement...

4803
03:34:48,140 --> 03:34:51,980
When he said it could be about the ad,

4804
03:34:51,980 --> 03:34:53,720
I didn't think...

4805
03:34:53,720 --> 03:34:54,920
it was too far-fetched.

4806
03:34:54,920 --> 03:34:56,450
I thought it was a good approach.

4807
03:34:57,390 --> 03:34:59,290
But what kept bothering me...

4808
03:35:01,590 --> 03:35:03,360
was the reason for the woman's existence.

4809
03:35:04,260 --> 03:35:07,430
(The reason for the woman's existence
in the 2nd image hint)

4810
03:35:07,430 --> 03:35:10,070
We had all this information,

4811
03:35:10,070 --> 03:35:12,400
and there must've been a reason
the woman was there.

4812
03:35:12,400 --> 03:35:14,400
Then how will this woman...

4813
03:35:14,400 --> 03:35:16,000
be used in the storyline?

4814
03:35:16,100 --> 03:35:17,470
We must come up with the reason.

4815
03:35:17,840 --> 03:35:19,670
I want to know why the woman
in the second image hunt...

4816
03:35:19,670 --> 03:35:21,840
was used as a hint.

4817
03:35:22,480 --> 03:35:24,380
- She didn't look too happy.
- Right.

4818
03:35:24,650 --> 03:35:25,780
There are many controversies...

4819
03:35:25,780 --> 03:35:26,920
- related to actors.
- Yes.

4820
03:35:27,680 --> 03:35:29,750
- The actor has a bad attitude.
- Yes.

4821
03:35:30,190 --> 03:35:32,720
So she looked unhappy...

4822
03:35:32,720 --> 03:35:34,960
when they took a photo together.

4823
03:35:35,120 --> 03:35:38,930
The reason the woman
looked at him unpleasantly...

4824
03:35:39,260 --> 03:35:43,230
could be because
the actor had a bad character.

4825
03:35:43,400 --> 03:35:46,130
Or because the actor did something...

4826
03:35:46,130 --> 03:35:48,270
to cause public rage,

4827
03:35:48,270 --> 03:35:50,310
she could've looked unpleasant.

4828
03:35:50,310 --> 03:35:51,370
That makes sense.

4829
03:35:51,840 --> 03:35:52,940
- The ad?
- Listen.

4830
03:35:52,940 --> 03:35:54,080
They signed an ad contract,

4831
03:35:54,080 --> 03:35:55,380
but he had a messy personal life.

4832
03:35:55,510 --> 03:35:57,080
Then the second image hint makes sense.

4833
03:35:57,080 --> 03:35:58,310
- All right.
- Then the third image hint...

4834
03:35:58,310 --> 03:35:59,510
is the problem.

4835
03:35:59,580 --> 03:36:00,850
The third image hint?

4836
03:36:01,020 --> 03:36:02,220
Oh, I figured it out.

4837
03:36:02,350 --> 03:36:04,850
The actor is the one in the ad.

4838
03:36:04,850 --> 03:36:05,920
They were removing the posters.

4839
03:36:05,920 --> 03:36:08,420
- Right!
- His scandal broke out.

4840
03:36:08,420 --> 03:36:10,360
They were removing all the posters.

4841
03:36:10,360 --> 03:36:11,960
But the movie's release date...

4842
03:36:11,960 --> 03:36:13,860
Anyway, it wasn't complete...

4843
03:36:13,860 --> 03:36:15,560
That should be our approach.

4844
03:36:15,800 --> 03:36:18,930
You Hyun thought the actor
had a messy private life.

4845
03:36:18,930 --> 03:36:20,740
That's what he said.

4846
03:36:21,040 --> 03:36:23,440
Seeing the image,

4847
03:36:23,440 --> 03:36:26,570
I thought a scandal broke out,

4848
03:36:26,570 --> 03:36:29,180
so they were removing the posters.
I could connect the story like that.

4849
03:36:29,180 --> 03:36:31,310
They have to pay the full penalty
if he's exposed.

4850
03:36:31,410 --> 03:36:33,210
So the agency...

4851
03:36:33,210 --> 03:36:35,320
thought they had to pay the full penalty
because of the actor.

4852
03:36:35,320 --> 03:36:37,190
That's why they killed their actor.

4853
03:36:38,290 --> 03:36:41,290
There was no word
that could satisfy the proposition.

4854
03:36:41,290 --> 03:36:42,860
But we had a specific hypothesis.

4855
03:36:42,860 --> 03:36:44,990
If that's the fact,
then this must be the keyword.

4856
03:36:45,890 --> 03:36:47,100
How many teams are in there?

4857
03:36:47,460 --> 03:36:48,900
- Is Team P1 in there?
- Team P1.

4858
03:36:50,170 --> 03:36:51,530
Gosh, they twisted it like that?

4859
03:36:53,030 --> 03:36:54,900
- Tae Gyun is in there, right?
- Yes, he's in there.

4860
03:36:54,970 --> 03:36:56,170
Oh, it's Team P1. We still have time,

4861
03:36:56,170 --> 03:36:57,210
so let me prepare the questions well.

4862
03:36:57,710 --> 03:36:59,610
I'll be outside getting some air.
Call me if you need me.

4863
03:37:00,240 --> 03:37:01,310
Darn it.

4864
03:37:09,750 --> 03:37:11,850
Lee Tae Gyun of Team P1...

4865
03:37:12,720 --> 03:37:14,060
has answered correctly.

4866
03:37:16,460 --> 03:37:19,130
The team members of Team P1,

4867
03:37:19,130 --> 03:37:20,860
please leave the main hall immediately.

4868
03:37:23,730 --> 03:37:25,970
We did it! We got it!

4869
03:37:32,670 --> 03:37:34,710
You guys formed an alliance, right?
You're all dead.

4870
03:37:38,180 --> 03:37:39,380
I didn't expect it at all.

4871
03:37:39,380 --> 03:37:41,050
I thought we'd win first place...

4872
03:37:41,050 --> 03:37:42,720
if we tried a few more times.

4873
03:37:42,720 --> 03:37:45,390
Then we heard they got the answer,
so we fell apart.

4874
03:37:45,550 --> 03:37:48,320
My heart started beating fast
all of a sudden.

4875
03:37:49,420 --> 03:37:51,360
If we go in now, we can get the answer.

4876
03:37:51,660 --> 03:37:53,090
- It's a bummer.
- We'll let Team C slide.

4877
03:37:54,630 --> 03:37:55,900
I thought it was nonsense.

4878
03:37:55,900 --> 03:37:58,430
We figured it out this fast,

4879
03:37:58,430 --> 03:38:00,540
but they got it faster than us?

4880
03:38:00,840 --> 03:38:04,240
I thought we could lose
to the alliance team,

4881
03:38:04,240 --> 03:38:07,140
but I had no idea
we could lose to Team P1.

4882
03:38:07,210 --> 03:38:09,110
But Team P1 got the answer fastest.

4883
03:38:09,440 --> 03:38:11,950
I thought Tae Gyun must be really good.

4884
03:38:14,350 --> 03:38:15,980
- Good luck.
- Good luck.

4885
03:38:19,990 --> 03:38:21,620
Was I surprised
when the correct answer came out?

4886
03:38:23,790 --> 03:38:24,860
No, I wasn't.

4887
03:38:27,130 --> 03:38:29,260
Whether that team wins first place
or our team does,

4888
03:38:30,670 --> 03:38:33,230
both outcomes work in my favor.

4889
03:38:34,540 --> 03:38:38,870
(An hour ago)

4890
03:38:39,310 --> 03:38:41,240
- Do you have anything to say to me?
- What?

4891
03:38:41,310 --> 03:38:43,340
- Do you have anything to say to me?
- I do.

4892
03:38:43,680 --> 03:38:48,080
- Be serious.
- You know that Team P2...

4893
03:38:48,080 --> 03:38:49,280
and Team R are working together, right?

4894
03:38:49,280 --> 03:38:50,490
Of course, I know that.

4895
03:38:50,490 --> 03:38:52,090
So why can't we work together too?

4896
03:38:52,790 --> 03:38:54,560
Right now,

4897
03:38:54,560 --> 03:38:57,330
you know an alliance is unnecessary.
It's meaningless.

4898
03:38:57,730 --> 03:38:59,330
But if you help me now,

4899
03:39:00,560 --> 03:39:02,660
I'll do whatever you want.

4900
03:39:03,430 --> 03:39:04,730
You know I mean by that, right?

4901
03:39:04,730 --> 03:39:07,400
Whether it's money or a vote ticket,

4902
03:39:07,400 --> 03:39:08,970
- Sure, okay.
- anything you want.

4903
03:39:08,970 --> 03:39:10,140
Just to save yourself.

4904
03:39:11,140 --> 03:39:13,210
Okay. Have you figured out a lot by now?

4905
03:39:13,210 --> 03:39:15,240
- No, not a lot.
- Did you pick up a few keywords?

4906
03:39:15,240 --> 03:39:16,240
No, I didn't.

4907
03:39:18,350 --> 03:39:19,350
Sang Min.

4908
03:39:21,380 --> 03:39:23,520
- Do you know the job yet? The job.
- What?

4909
03:39:23,890 --> 03:39:26,690
- No, I don't.
- Then I'll tell you what the job is.

4910
03:39:26,690 --> 03:39:28,620
But you have to keep me alive
however you can if I become...

4911
03:39:28,620 --> 03:39:30,190
- the Deathmatch candidate later.
- Okay.

4912
03:39:31,190 --> 03:39:32,190
The job is stuntman.

4913
03:39:36,400 --> 03:39:37,670
Hey, Tae Gyun. Come here.

4914
03:39:38,130 --> 03:39:39,830
It felt like that team...

4915
03:39:39,830 --> 03:39:42,170
really wasn't making any progress.

4916
03:39:42,170 --> 03:39:44,040
So I told him that the job was stuntman,

4917
03:39:44,040 --> 03:39:45,840
and he walked away
looking incredibly happy.

4918
03:39:45,840 --> 03:39:47,940
It made me feel proud inside.

4919
03:39:48,210 --> 03:39:51,150
(A little later, Sang Min called
Kyoung Hoon over again.)

4920
03:39:51,150 --> 03:39:52,750
- I've figured out a lot now.
- Okay.

4921
03:39:53,580 --> 03:39:56,920
Tell me what you know.

4922
03:39:56,920 --> 03:39:57,950
I'll save you no matter what.

4923
03:39:58,150 --> 03:39:59,790
You know that the actor...

4924
03:39:59,790 --> 03:40:01,160
You know that the actor
was the intended target, right?

4925
03:40:01,890 --> 03:40:03,020
Okay.

4926
03:40:03,020 --> 03:40:04,460
It was the actor who was supposed to die.

4927
03:40:05,090 --> 03:40:07,060
- So?
- The actor was supposed to die,

4928
03:40:07,060 --> 03:40:08,360
but this one was killed instead
by mistake.

4929
03:40:09,100 --> 03:40:11,030
So was the actor
trying to kill the stuntman?

4930
03:40:11,030 --> 03:40:12,570
Or was the stuntman
trying to kill the actor?

4931
03:40:12,570 --> 03:40:13,570
It was a third party.

4932
03:40:13,570 --> 03:40:14,870
Okay, so a third party was...

4933
03:40:14,870 --> 03:40:16,840
- Trying to kill the actor.
- Trying to kill the actor?

4934
03:40:16,840 --> 03:40:17,840
- Yes.
- Are you sure?

4935
03:40:17,840 --> 03:40:19,570
- Yes.
- Did you ask this?

4936
03:40:20,940 --> 03:40:22,880
This is a team game.

4937
03:40:22,880 --> 03:40:26,010
How is he giving us
his team's information?

4938
03:40:26,380 --> 03:40:28,350
Even his own teammates...

4939
03:40:28,680 --> 03:40:31,020
shouldn't trust Kyoung Hoon too easily.

4940
03:40:31,050 --> 03:40:32,820
He's truly an unpredictable person.

4941
03:40:32,850 --> 03:40:35,620
Well, I'd basically taken out
an insurance policy...

4942
03:40:35,620 --> 03:40:37,290
in case I didn't win.

4943
03:40:37,390 --> 03:40:40,060
And this insurance...

4944
03:40:40,060 --> 03:40:42,230
wasn't just for this one game.

4945
03:40:42,230 --> 03:40:44,230
It was something that would...

4946
03:40:44,230 --> 03:40:47,870
affect the upcoming rounds as well.

4947
03:40:47,870 --> 03:40:49,970
So it was extremely valuable.

4948
03:40:49,970 --> 03:40:52,810
That's why it didn't matter to me
whether our team won...

4949
03:40:52,810 --> 03:40:53,980
or their team won.

4950
03:40:55,080 --> 03:40:56,950
We have to figure out who.

4951
03:40:57,050 --> 03:40:58,550
- Who and why.
- Who and why.

4952
03:40:59,180 --> 03:41:01,220
So like I said,

4953
03:41:01,220 --> 03:41:03,720
the stuntman and the actor could be women.

4954
03:41:04,620 --> 03:41:08,590
If the stuntman were a woman,

4955
03:41:08,590 --> 03:41:10,490
- the breasts and...
- Right.

4956
03:41:10,690 --> 03:41:12,230
- But...
- We get it.

4957
03:41:13,660 --> 03:41:16,060
He's fixated on that.

4958
03:41:16,760 --> 03:41:20,170
What does the fact that the ad changed
actually mean?

4959
03:41:20,700 --> 03:41:24,670
They're shooting a new ad now.

4960
03:41:24,670 --> 03:41:27,810
When Sang Min brought up the idea
that there was...

4961
03:41:27,810 --> 03:41:29,440
something in the ad hint,

4962
03:41:29,440 --> 03:41:31,650
I thought that
the ad itself could be a keyword...

4963
03:41:31,650 --> 03:41:33,880
and that we would need to ask
a question about this.

4964
03:41:37,620 --> 03:41:38,690
Sir!

4965
03:41:42,360 --> 03:41:43,560
Would you like to ask a question?

4966
03:41:43,930 --> 03:41:45,230
Yes, I'll ask a question.

4967
03:41:50,500 --> 03:41:51,900
What team just went inside?

4968
03:41:52,030 --> 03:41:53,500
- Team P1?
- Team P1.

4969
03:41:55,040 --> 03:41:59,440
Is the reason why the person
trying to murder the male actor...

4970
03:42:00,110 --> 03:42:02,410
was under time pressure...

4971
03:42:03,040 --> 03:42:05,810
related to the ad...

4972
03:42:06,450 --> 03:42:08,680
the male actor had shot?

4973
03:42:10,390 --> 03:42:11,520
Yes, that is correct.

4974
03:42:13,190 --> 03:42:14,560
It's related to the ad.

4975
03:42:14,720 --> 03:42:16,220
But then, the first hint...

4976
03:42:16,520 --> 03:42:17,530
(The culprit was under time pressure.)

4977
03:42:17,530 --> 03:42:20,300
The culprit was under time pressure.

4978
03:42:22,430 --> 03:42:25,970
It's related to the ad
and the person had to kill him quickly.

4979
03:42:26,300 --> 03:42:29,800
It's related to the ad
and the person didn't have much time.

4980
03:42:30,070 --> 03:42:32,770
The actor had to die
before the ad went live.

4981
03:42:33,010 --> 03:42:34,140
(The culprit committed the crime
to prevent a significant loss.)

4982
03:42:34,140 --> 03:42:36,510
To prevent a significant loss,
the person had to kill him quickly.

4983
03:42:37,080 --> 03:42:39,510
The person was under time pressure
to prevent a loss.

4984
03:42:39,910 --> 03:42:42,980
If the ad goes out,
it will result in a loss.

4985
03:42:43,050 --> 03:42:44,720
And to prevent that huge loss,

4986
03:42:44,720 --> 03:42:46,390
the person had to kill the actor
before the ad was aired.

4987
03:42:46,390 --> 03:42:48,790
Then who benefits...

4988
03:42:48,860 --> 03:42:50,530
when the ad doesn't air?

4989
03:42:51,960 --> 03:42:52,960
Penalty fee?

4990
03:42:56,000 --> 03:42:57,730
If the person killed the actor,
they wouldn't have to pay the penalty fee.

4991
03:42:59,870 --> 03:43:00,970
I thought...

4992
03:43:01,370 --> 03:43:04,570
most of the teams were close
to the correct answer.

4993
03:43:05,910 --> 03:43:08,040
If I don't get the answer here,

4994
03:43:08,310 --> 03:43:10,450
I thought the next team might...

4995
03:43:10,450 --> 03:43:12,680
finish the game during this turn.

4996
03:43:13,380 --> 03:43:14,850
I'd like to call out my answer.

4997
03:43:18,690 --> 03:43:19,790
Steve is...

4998
03:43:19,790 --> 03:43:21,520
(Lee Tae Gyun's answer)

4999
03:43:21,520 --> 03:43:24,830
a person whose profession is a stuntman.

5000
03:43:26,290 --> 03:43:29,500
Because the male actor caused trouble,

5001
03:43:30,160 --> 03:43:32,200
the male actor's agency...

5002
03:43:32,670 --> 03:43:33,800
was put in a situation...

5003
03:43:34,640 --> 03:43:37,840
where they had to pay a penalty fee
to the ad company.

5004
03:43:38,970 --> 03:43:41,340
To avoid paying that penalty,

5005
03:43:42,040 --> 03:43:44,950
the male actor's agency...

5006
03:43:45,280 --> 03:43:49,120
came up with a plan to kill the actor.

5007
03:43:49,950 --> 03:43:53,960
And in order to kill him, the agency...

5008
03:43:54,990 --> 03:43:58,390
punctured the rear tire
of the motorcycle...

5009
03:43:58,830 --> 03:44:02,160
the actor was using for filming.

5010
03:44:03,560 --> 03:44:07,900
But Steve, the stuntman...

5011
03:44:08,570 --> 03:44:12,910
who stood in for the male actor
during dangerous scenes,

5012
03:44:13,340 --> 03:44:16,910
ended up riding that punctured motorcycle,

5013
03:44:17,040 --> 03:44:19,410
crashed, and died in the accident.

5014
03:44:24,090 --> 03:44:25,220
That is correct.

5015
03:44:26,520 --> 03:44:27,920
He got the correct answer.

5016
03:44:27,920 --> 03:44:33,560
(All members of Team P1
are guaranteed survival as 2nd place.)

5017
03:44:40,940 --> 03:44:43,400
I literally got goosebumps
all over my body.

5018
03:44:43,500 --> 03:44:46,140
I felt proud, and our entire team
created this result together.

5019
03:44:46,440 --> 03:44:47,940
We crushed it.

5020
03:44:48,380 --> 03:44:49,940
I'm glad we got second place.

5021
03:44:49,940 --> 03:44:52,280
There's not much difference
between 1st and 2nd place anyway.

5022
03:44:52,280 --> 03:44:53,510
What matters is that everyone survives.

5023
03:44:54,020 --> 03:44:55,420
I guess I'm not going home today.

5024
03:44:55,950 --> 03:44:57,120
I'm so happy.

5025
03:44:57,890 --> 03:44:59,720
Watch out, Team P3.

5026
03:45:00,090 --> 03:45:01,120
(Penalty fee)

5027
03:45:01,120 --> 03:45:05,530
(Scandal)

5028
03:45:05,530 --> 03:45:07,500
(Team P1, 2nd place,
All members are guaranteed survival)

5029
03:45:07,500 --> 03:45:09,900
(The player with the least time spent
becomes a Deathmatch candidate.)

5030
03:45:09,900 --> 03:45:12,300
(The player with the most time spent
is confirmed for the Deathmatch.)

5031
03:45:15,400 --> 03:45:17,970
Assuming you don't come in last,

5032
03:45:17,970 --> 03:45:20,640
how is your team planning to choose
your Deathmatch candidate?

5033
03:45:20,640 --> 03:45:22,510
We deliberately avoided discussing it.

5034
03:45:22,680 --> 03:45:23,980
But we do need to decide.

5035
03:45:23,980 --> 03:45:25,080
I'm getting hit with reality right now.

5036
03:45:25,710 --> 03:45:27,620
In the end, we failed to place 1st or 2nd,

5037
03:45:27,620 --> 03:45:29,680
so we have to prepare
to be 3rd, 4th, or 5th place.

5038
03:45:30,380 --> 03:45:32,520
You don't want to go again, do you?

5039
03:45:32,520 --> 03:45:34,790
It's not that I don't want to go.

5040
03:45:34,820 --> 03:45:37,290
But since it's confirmed...

5041
03:45:37,290 --> 03:45:39,260
that three people
from our team have to go,

5042
03:45:39,260 --> 03:45:41,530
I'm worried about whether
we should send our best player...

5043
03:45:41,530 --> 03:45:43,300
and how I should think it through...

5044
03:45:43,300 --> 03:45:45,470
and explain it to the team.

5045
03:45:45,470 --> 03:45:47,670
It's not that
I'm just trying to save myself.

5046
03:45:48,440 --> 03:45:49,970
You're trying to consider
what would be more helpful to the team.

5047
03:45:49,970 --> 03:45:52,310
We couldn't help but feel anxious,

5048
03:45:52,310 --> 03:45:53,810
because now that
second place had been taken,

5049
03:45:54,010 --> 03:45:55,340
an elimination candidate had to come...

5050
03:45:55,340 --> 03:45:56,740
from each of the three remaining teams.

5051
03:45:56,740 --> 03:45:58,910
So from that point on, Gwan Hee...

5052
03:45:58,910 --> 03:46:01,020
suggested that we discuss...

5053
03:46:01,020 --> 03:46:03,180
who should go to the Deathmatch.

5054
03:46:03,180 --> 03:46:06,990
Since one of us has to go
to the Deathmatch anyway,

5055
03:46:06,990 --> 03:46:09,160
I wanted to have it settled.

5056
03:46:09,160 --> 03:46:10,630
(Gwan Hee gathered
all of Team R and Team P2.)

5057
03:46:10,630 --> 03:46:11,830
Yes, please go ahead.

5058
03:46:11,830 --> 03:46:15,160
First of all, as I feared,

5059
03:46:15,160 --> 03:46:18,630
each of our teams must send
one Deathmatch candidate.

5060
03:46:18,630 --> 03:46:23,200
So if you could share with us
how you plan to...

5061
03:46:23,200 --> 03:46:24,670
choose your Deathmatch candidate...

5062
03:46:24,670 --> 03:46:25,840
We really don't have any plans.

5063
03:46:25,840 --> 03:46:28,280
We can't decide the candidate right now...

5064
03:46:28,280 --> 03:46:29,440
because of the time.

5065
03:46:29,440 --> 03:46:31,710
- I know, but discussing beforehand...
- Let's go.

5066
03:46:31,950 --> 03:46:34,380
(Frustrated)

5067
03:46:34,380 --> 03:46:35,820
Even now, I still...

5068
03:46:36,220 --> 03:46:39,450
had a small suspicion...

5069
03:46:39,720 --> 03:46:42,620
that Beom had adjusted the time...

5070
03:46:42,860 --> 03:46:46,030
and strategized for his own survival.

5071
03:46:46,330 --> 03:46:47,630
And as for the questions,

5072
03:46:48,160 --> 03:46:49,830
since Seung Yong is good at asking them,

5073
03:46:49,830 --> 03:46:51,270
he should handle all of them...

5074
03:46:51,270 --> 03:46:52,530
and submit the answer too.

5075
03:46:52,530 --> 03:46:54,200
That means he gets the most time.

5076
03:46:54,200 --> 03:46:57,310
But also, if we fail to place even second,

5077
03:46:57,310 --> 03:46:58,440
I think we have to make a choice.

5078
03:46:58,440 --> 03:46:59,970
You're saying we should think about
who should go?

5079
03:46:59,970 --> 03:47:04,110
Yes. Whether it be Seung Yong or me...

5080
03:47:04,110 --> 03:47:05,850
I'll do it. I'll go to the Deathmatch.

5081
03:47:05,850 --> 03:47:07,320
Yes, so we have to decide.

5082
03:47:07,320 --> 03:47:09,450
- Let's not think about that.
- Our times are pretty similar.

5083
03:47:10,050 --> 03:47:11,120
When I thought about it,

5084
03:47:12,190 --> 03:47:15,820
it was pretty much a fact that
I'd barely asked any questions.

5085
03:47:16,190 --> 03:47:19,430
It was also a fact that
Seung Yong used the most time.

5086
03:47:19,630 --> 03:47:22,060
And I knew that
Beom was right in the middle...

5087
03:47:22,060 --> 03:47:23,360
between us.

5088
03:47:23,800 --> 03:47:27,230
But he was saying that...

5089
03:47:27,230 --> 03:47:28,770
he wants to go to the Deathmatch.

5090
03:47:28,770 --> 03:47:30,040
As the game kept moving forward,

5091
03:47:30,040 --> 03:47:33,070
if he really wanted to go, he should have
either committed to becoming last place...

5092
03:47:33,240 --> 03:47:35,140
or at least thought about...

5093
03:47:35,140 --> 03:47:38,710
a 3rd or 4th place strategy.

5094
03:47:38,710 --> 03:47:41,380
It's what I said from the beginning.

5095
03:47:41,380 --> 03:47:43,580
That the three of us should
first agree on...

5096
03:47:43,850 --> 03:47:46,490
who should go to the Deathmatch.

5097
03:47:46,490 --> 03:47:47,690
I don't mind going myself.

5098
03:47:47,690 --> 03:47:48,690
I don't mind going myself either.

5099
03:47:48,690 --> 03:47:51,160
You say you'd go,

5100
03:47:51,160 --> 03:47:52,790
but the three of us
are in different positions.

5101
03:47:52,790 --> 03:47:54,930
I just want us to be aligned on this.

5102
03:47:57,000 --> 03:47:58,700
About the answer?

5103
03:47:59,930 --> 03:48:02,140
During that conversation,

5104
03:48:02,140 --> 03:48:04,170
I felt like he was tuning me out.

5105
03:48:04,240 --> 03:48:07,110
I was mentally preparing myself
for it to be either me or Seung Yong.

5106
03:48:08,910 --> 03:48:10,010
Hello.

5107
03:48:10,010 --> 03:48:11,110
(Meanwhile, Team C's Kang Ji Hoo
enters the Voting Room.)

5108
03:48:11,110 --> 03:48:12,410
Would you like to ask a question?

5109
03:48:12,410 --> 03:48:14,550
First, I'll use our keyword reveal pass.

5110
03:48:14,550 --> 03:48:16,850
Please state the keyword you want.

5111
03:48:16,850 --> 03:48:18,520
The keyword is penalty fee.

5112
03:48:18,950 --> 03:48:20,520
The keyword "penalty fee" is...

5113
03:48:21,460 --> 03:48:22,590
correct.

5114
03:48:24,390 --> 03:48:26,390
Does the actor
the culprit was trying to murder...

5115
03:48:26,390 --> 03:48:28,260
have personal life issues?

5116
03:48:28,530 --> 03:48:29,830
Yes, that is correct.

5117
03:48:30,670 --> 03:48:32,000
I'd like to call out my answer.

5118
03:48:33,930 --> 03:48:37,270
The actor whom
Stuntman Steve was a double for.

5119
03:48:37,670 --> 03:48:41,540
Thinking a scandal regarding this actor's
personal life would soon break out,

5120
03:48:41,540 --> 03:48:44,050
the head of the actor's agency wanted to
avoid paying a penalty fee for his ad.

5121
03:48:44,050 --> 03:48:47,450
So in an attempt to murder the actor
before the scandal broke out,

5122
03:48:47,780 --> 03:48:49,820
he sabotaged the motorcycle's brakes.

5123
03:48:50,280 --> 03:48:53,050
But on the day of filming,
the actor didn't show up...

5124
03:48:53,590 --> 03:48:56,760
and Stuntman Steve filmed in his place.

5125
03:48:56,760 --> 03:48:58,190
While riding that motorcycle,

5126
03:48:58,290 --> 03:49:01,360
he couldn't stop
due to the broken brakes...

5127
03:49:01,360 --> 03:49:03,030
and died in a crash.

5128
03:49:08,640 --> 03:49:11,270
Kang Ji Hoo got the correct answer.

5129
03:49:11,610 --> 03:49:15,180
(Team C is 3rd place.)

5130
03:49:15,180 --> 03:49:16,180
We're safe.

5131
03:49:21,280 --> 03:49:23,420
It's a bit disappointing.

5132
03:49:23,420 --> 03:49:25,120
Still, I hated seeing
those two teams form an alliance.

5133
03:49:25,420 --> 03:49:27,960
So the fact that
the teams that didn't ally won...

5134
03:49:27,960 --> 03:49:29,920
felt incredibly satisfying,
since we won purely on skill.

5135
03:49:30,160 --> 03:49:31,390
It was very satisfying.

5136
03:49:31,660 --> 03:49:33,230
(Team C, 3rd place)

5137
03:49:33,230 --> 03:49:36,260
(The player with the least time spent
becomes a Deathmatch candidate.)

5138
03:49:36,430 --> 03:49:37,530
(The Team P2-Team R alliance
feels deflated.)

5139
03:49:37,530 --> 03:49:38,830
No!

5140
03:49:39,130 --> 03:49:40,400
This can't be happening.

5141
03:49:40,630 --> 03:49:42,470
Now it's down to our two teams.

5142
03:49:42,470 --> 03:49:44,440
We have the same amount
of information, though.

5143
03:49:44,840 --> 03:49:46,140
My mind went blank.

5144
03:49:46,670 --> 03:49:49,510
What's funny is, the two allied teams...

5145
03:49:49,510 --> 03:49:51,550
have to place 4th and 5th side by side.

5146
03:49:51,550 --> 03:49:53,310
How pathetic and embarrassing is that?

5147
03:49:53,610 --> 03:49:55,350
But whatever happens,
we can't place fifth, right?

5148
03:49:55,350 --> 03:49:57,050
We have to at least
get fourth place somehow.

5149
03:49:57,050 --> 03:50:00,550
What could be the material benefit?

5150
03:50:00,720 --> 03:50:01,820
This is a team game.

5151
03:50:04,460 --> 03:50:06,960
The third extra hint will be revealed.

5152
03:50:08,500 --> 03:50:10,330
Steve's death...

5153
03:50:10,330 --> 03:50:12,630
was quickly buried by even bigger news.

5154
03:50:14,940 --> 03:50:16,570
I think I got it.

5155
03:50:16,840 --> 03:50:18,940
- Really?
- He said "even bigger news."

5156
03:50:19,110 --> 03:50:21,840
When it comes to celebrity news,
what's the biggest kind of story there is?

5157
03:50:21,840 --> 03:50:23,040
- Drugs?
- Dating rumors.

5158
03:50:24,250 --> 03:50:25,910
And to make sure
that story doesn't get out,

5159
03:50:25,910 --> 03:50:27,310
the culprit tried to kill him.

5160
03:50:27,310 --> 03:50:28,720
Gosh, that's brutal.

5161
03:50:28,820 --> 03:50:29,820
And then what?

5162
03:50:29,820 --> 03:50:31,020
The actor must have been pressuring him...

5163
03:50:31,020 --> 03:50:32,290
because that's when
the relationship started to go wrong.

5164
03:50:32,450 --> 03:50:35,120
The agency CEO must have been
under time pressure.

5165
03:50:35,290 --> 03:50:37,690
If money was the motive for the murder,

5166
03:50:37,930 --> 03:50:40,390
the question is what kind of money it was.

5167
03:50:40,690 --> 03:50:42,830
If a huge amount of money was on the line,

5168
03:50:42,960 --> 03:50:46,970
it could have been because of
a clause in the contract.

5169
03:50:46,970 --> 03:50:48,440
I'll ask first.

5170
03:50:48,440 --> 03:50:53,340
(With one small clue in mind,
he enters the Voting Room.)

5171
03:50:55,740 --> 03:50:57,140
We have to avoid fifth place.

5172
03:50:57,140 --> 03:50:59,150
Being 4th place is practically
the same as being 2nd place.

5173
03:51:00,250 --> 03:51:01,720
You're right.

5174
03:51:01,720 --> 03:51:02,980
We'd have immunity if we placed fourth.

5175
03:51:02,980 --> 03:51:04,290
We're doomed if we place fifth.

5176
03:51:04,290 --> 03:51:05,350
We'd have no choice but to go.

5177
03:51:10,090 --> 03:51:12,590
(Thinking)

5178
03:51:14,400 --> 03:51:15,500
Does the actor...

5179
03:51:17,130 --> 03:51:19,400
currently have any endorsement deals?

5180
03:51:19,630 --> 03:51:21,000
Yes, that is correct.

5181
03:51:22,270 --> 03:51:25,070
If the actor does something wrong
and ends up having to pay a penalty fee,

5182
03:51:25,370 --> 03:51:27,370
does the agency CEO
have to pay it as well?

5183
03:51:27,740 --> 03:51:29,110
Yes, that is correct.

5184
03:51:30,440 --> 03:51:32,280
I'd like to call out my answer.

5185
03:51:32,510 --> 03:51:35,850
The actor Steve works
as a stunt double for...

5186
03:51:36,220 --> 03:51:38,520
is currently appearing in an ad.

5187
03:51:38,720 --> 03:51:40,890
The actor did something wrong...

5188
03:51:40,890 --> 03:51:44,530
and will have to pay a penalty fee.

5189
03:51:44,530 --> 03:51:48,260
The agency CEO wanted to prevent
a situation where he would also...

5190
03:51:48,260 --> 03:51:49,760
have to pay the penalty fee.

5191
03:51:49,760 --> 03:51:52,630
So before that could happen,

5192
03:51:52,630 --> 03:51:55,300
he sabotaged the motorcycle...

5193
03:51:55,300 --> 03:51:59,610
in an attempt to kill the actor on set.

5194
03:51:59,810 --> 03:52:03,980
But since Steve stepped in
for the actor as the stuntman,

5195
03:52:04,140 --> 03:52:06,380
Steve ended up dying instead.

5196
03:52:07,380 --> 03:52:08,520
That is correct.

5197
03:52:10,750 --> 03:52:12,820
Time has now stopped for all teams.

5198
03:52:13,220 --> 03:52:14,460
Thank you.

5199
03:52:19,790 --> 03:52:22,630
Shin Seung Yong got the correct answer.

5200
03:52:24,000 --> 03:52:26,100
(Team R is 4th place.)

5201
03:52:26,100 --> 03:52:27,570
Was it dating rumors?

5202
03:52:27,570 --> 03:52:28,770
No. This was so simple,

5203
03:52:28,770 --> 03:52:30,700
but I think we overcomplicated it.

5204
03:52:31,170 --> 03:52:34,340
The whole reason we formed an alliance...

5205
03:52:34,340 --> 03:52:37,950
was to place 1st or 2nd in Round 2.

5206
03:52:38,450 --> 03:52:40,710
But since we barely managed
to get fourth place,

5207
03:52:40,710 --> 03:52:43,550
it meant another person from our team
could be eliminated.

5208
03:52:43,550 --> 03:52:45,390
This was another total defeat for us.

5209
03:52:45,490 --> 03:52:47,250
I guess we're just really bad at games.

5210
03:52:47,390 --> 03:52:49,820
The end of this alliance...

5211
03:52:50,260 --> 03:52:52,830
can be summed up in just one word.

5212
03:52:53,690 --> 03:52:54,760
A blunder.

5213
03:52:55,430 --> 03:52:57,730
Mystery Time is now over.

5214
03:52:59,830 --> 03:53:00,940
Good job.

5215
03:53:26,260 --> 03:53:28,260
Even though we got the right answer…

5216
03:53:28,260 --> 03:53:30,060
in the end,

5217
03:53:30,330 --> 03:53:33,270
I felt like...

5218
03:53:33,270 --> 03:53:35,700
we could have approached the problem
in a much simpler way.

5219
03:53:35,700 --> 03:53:37,970
I was upset because...

5220
03:53:38,210 --> 03:53:40,370
we failed to do that.

5221
03:53:40,840 --> 03:53:42,980
I was also really sorry to my teammates.

5222
03:53:46,410 --> 03:53:48,950
(Sighing)

5223
03:53:48,950 --> 03:53:49,950
Why are you crying?

5224
03:53:57,830 --> 03:53:59,990
- Are you frustrated?
- No.

5225
03:54:14,140 --> 03:54:15,380
It's just so disappointing.

5226
03:54:20,310 --> 03:54:22,120
From Seung Yong's perspective,

5227
03:54:22,180 --> 03:54:24,820
I can understand how he's feeling.

5228
03:54:24,950 --> 03:54:27,790
The frustration, the bitterness.

5229
03:54:27,990 --> 03:54:30,620
He didn't come here
to end up looking like this.

5230
03:54:30,920 --> 03:54:33,290
From the very first game,
he went to the survival grounds,

5231
03:54:33,430 --> 03:54:35,000
then to the Deathmatch.

5232
03:54:35,200 --> 03:54:37,560
He wanted to do well
in the Money Challenge.

5233
03:54:37,730 --> 03:54:40,330
But when even that didn't work out,
he got so upset that he started crying.

5234
03:54:48,740 --> 03:54:51,310
Since I'm the older one on the team,
I felt incredibly sorry...

5235
03:54:52,480 --> 03:54:54,420
and foolish.

5236
03:55:07,530 --> 03:55:10,500
I wanted to prove to my teammates
that I could do well in this.

5237
03:55:13,300 --> 03:55:15,040
They really trusted me...

5238
03:55:15,040 --> 03:55:17,440
in the process of
working through this game.

5239
03:55:19,910 --> 03:55:21,940
This wasn't a game we should have lost.

5240
03:55:25,110 --> 03:55:27,480
People probably already...

5241
03:55:27,480 --> 03:55:30,680
thought our team was weak,
and then the results...

5242
03:55:31,120 --> 03:55:33,320
really did make us look like a weak team.

5243
03:55:33,320 --> 03:55:35,160
That was just so frustrating...

5244
03:55:35,320 --> 03:55:36,520
and infuriating.

5245
03:55:36,520 --> 03:55:39,560
It made me wonder
if this is really all I'm capable of.

5246
03:55:50,300 --> 03:55:55,740
(Today's Money Challenge is over.)

5247
03:55:55,740 --> 03:55:58,310
The results of the Money Challenge
will be announced.

5248
03:55:59,380 --> 03:56:02,950
Today's winning team is Team P3.

5249
03:56:03,050 --> 03:56:06,620
Team P3 will receive 50,000 dollars
in team funds,

5250
03:56:06,620 --> 03:56:11,560
along with an elimination immunity pass
and an extra vote ticket.

5251
03:56:12,130 --> 03:56:14,190
A representative of
the winning team, Team P3,

5252
03:56:14,190 --> 03:56:16,060
please enter
the Voting Room immediately...

5253
03:56:16,060 --> 03:56:18,770
to collect the 50,000 dollars.

5254
03:56:22,140 --> 03:56:23,640
Gosh, that's a lot of money.

5255
03:56:23,940 --> 03:56:26,670
The prize money for winning
the Money Challenge is 50,000 dollars.

5256
03:56:26,940 --> 03:56:28,540
The extra vote ticket...

5257
03:56:28,540 --> 03:56:30,780
can be used during the vote for
elimination candidates,

5258
03:56:30,780 --> 03:56:33,380
and only one team member may use it.

5259
03:56:33,780 --> 03:56:37,250
Victory is so sweet it could rot my teeth.

5260
03:56:37,250 --> 03:56:38,720
I'm so happy.

5261
03:56:39,020 --> 03:56:40,920
I'm already grateful just for
the elimination immunity pass,

5262
03:56:40,920 --> 03:56:43,160
but to give us money
and an extra vote ticket?

5263
03:56:43,360 --> 03:56:44,960
The results speak for themselves.

5264
03:56:45,190 --> 03:56:47,330
Team P3 is a complete package as a team.

5265
03:56:48,200 --> 03:56:51,000
Next, the lowest-ranking team
will be announced.

5266
03:56:51,770 --> 03:56:55,440
The lowest-ranking team,
placing fifth in the Mystery Time,

5267
03:56:58,440 --> 03:56:59,870
is Team P2.

5268
03:57:00,840 --> 03:57:03,580
Once
the elimination candidate vote is over,

5269
03:57:03,580 --> 03:57:06,380
Team P2 will move to
the outdoor survival grounds immediately.

5270
03:57:06,780 --> 03:57:09,080
All I could think was, "We're doomed."

5271
03:57:09,250 --> 03:57:12,320
The player on Team P2 with
the most accumulated time...

5272
03:57:12,890 --> 03:57:14,690
will go straight to the Deathmatch.

5273
03:57:15,720 --> 03:57:17,890
I'd been in and out of the Voting Room
so many times...

5274
03:57:17,890 --> 03:57:21,800
that I figured I would probably be
the one going to the Deathmatch.

5275
03:57:22,030 --> 03:57:24,260
Actually, in our team,

5276
03:57:24,260 --> 03:57:26,830
Seung Jin always said he would go,

5277
03:57:26,830 --> 03:57:30,070
and he was also the one
asking the most questions.

5278
03:57:30,470 --> 03:57:32,640
The player going straight
to the Deathmatch is...

5279
03:57:40,980 --> 03:57:42,050
(Hyun Sung Joo)

5280
03:57:42,050 --> 03:57:45,620
Hyun Sung Joo.

5281
03:57:48,220 --> 03:57:49,490
I expected it.

5282
03:57:49,960 --> 03:57:52,530
Instead of thinking about
complicated things, I spent time…

5283
03:57:52,530 --> 03:57:54,160
focusing on improving our ranking.

5284
03:57:54,460 --> 03:57:59,130
(While the Mystery Time was in progress,)

5285
03:58:00,930 --> 03:58:05,240
(Hyun Sung Joo spent the most time
in the Time Room among Team P2.)

5286
03:58:05,240 --> 03:58:07,140
While I did that,

5287
03:58:07,140 --> 03:58:08,340
we ended up in last place.

5288
03:58:08,540 --> 03:58:10,610
There are four people on the team,

5289
03:58:10,610 --> 03:58:12,350
and we have to take turns sacrificing.

5290
03:58:12,350 --> 03:58:14,150
Since Jin Hyeong already went once,

5291
03:58:14,350 --> 03:58:15,750
I figured, "All right, you went once."

5292
03:58:15,750 --> 03:58:18,290
"And now it's my turn
to be the second person to go."

5293
03:58:18,290 --> 03:58:19,550
It's fair.

5294
03:58:19,550 --> 03:58:21,150
(Final accumulated time)

5295
03:58:21,150 --> 03:58:23,990
(Lee Jin Hyeong, YunB,
Ha Seung Jin, Hyun Sung Joo)

5296
03:58:25,860 --> 03:58:28,500
There is one additional announcement.

5297
03:58:29,130 --> 03:58:32,030
If the elimination occurs
in Team Rookie today,

5298
03:58:32,900 --> 03:58:34,530
the survivor of the Deathmatch...

5299
03:58:34,700 --> 03:58:37,240
will be transferred to Team Rookie.

5300
03:58:37,600 --> 03:58:38,670
- What?
- Gosh.

5301
03:58:39,740 --> 03:58:40,940
That's not bad.

5302
03:58:41,240 --> 03:58:44,110
I don't mean that
receiving a new teammate isn't bad.

5303
03:58:44,280 --> 03:58:45,980
But so far, we were the only team
with three people.

5304
03:58:46,610 --> 03:58:48,420
And now, another team will have
three people too.

5305
03:58:49,220 --> 03:58:51,850
Bloody Game is so complicated.

5306
03:58:51,850 --> 03:58:55,560
It's disgusting.
The way it's designed is disgusting.

5307
03:58:57,290 --> 03:58:59,960
Hyun Sung Joo,
please leave the main hall immediately...

5308
03:58:59,960 --> 03:59:01,760
and prepare for the Deathmatch.

5309
03:59:01,960 --> 03:59:03,530
- Bye.
- You got this.

5310
03:59:03,530 --> 03:59:04,530
Sung Joo, you got this!

5311
03:59:04,600 --> 03:59:05,600
See you.

5312
03:59:05,600 --> 03:59:07,600
- You got this.
- See you in a bit.

5313
03:59:12,070 --> 03:59:14,310
I should have been more proactive.

5314
03:59:15,280 --> 03:59:16,640
Gosh.

5315
03:59:17,940 --> 03:59:20,250
The guilt I felt was beyond words.

5316
03:59:21,520 --> 03:59:24,350
Now, the elimination candidates
will be announced.

5317
03:59:24,820 --> 03:59:27,750
Team P1, which finished in second place,

5318
03:59:28,090 --> 03:59:30,520
will all be safe from elimination.

5319
03:59:32,230 --> 03:59:35,830
From Team Challenger and Team Rookie,
which finished 3rd and 4th respectively,

5320
03:59:36,500 --> 03:59:39,500
the player with
the least accumulated time...

5321
03:59:39,500 --> 03:59:40,930
will become the elimination candidate.

5322
03:59:42,040 --> 03:59:44,710
I thought I would become
our Deathmatch candidate...

5323
03:59:44,710 --> 03:59:46,140
because at the very end,

5324
03:59:46,140 --> 03:59:48,380
You Hyun suddenly went in
and asked a few questions.

5325
03:59:48,710 --> 03:59:50,580
This is the worst. I'm doomed.

5326
03:59:51,010 --> 03:59:54,510
The elimination candidate from
Team Challenger, which finished third,

5327
03:59:56,650 --> 03:59:57,650
(Kim You Hyun)

5328
03:59:57,650 --> 04:00:00,720
is Kim You Hyun.

5329
04:00:01,120 --> 04:00:03,090
From the moment Round Two started,

5330
04:00:03,090 --> 04:00:06,290
I already thought there was over
a 90 percent chance it would be me.

5331
04:00:06,660 --> 04:00:08,460
(Final accumulated time)

5332
04:00:08,460 --> 04:00:10,800
(Kim You Hyun, Kim Kyoung Hoon,
Kim Nam Hee, Kang Ji Hoo)

5333
04:00:10,800 --> 04:00:14,130
The elimination candidate from
Team Rookie, which finished fourth is...

5334
04:00:16,370 --> 04:00:18,000
I can't. I can't go.

5335
04:00:18,940 --> 04:00:20,570
My heart was pounding.

5336
04:00:21,170 --> 04:00:24,540
Lee Gwan Hee.

5337
04:00:27,380 --> 04:00:29,220
When my name popped up on the screen,

5338
04:00:29,220 --> 04:00:31,080
my heart sank.

5339
04:00:31,920 --> 04:00:33,990
(Final accumulated time)

5340
04:00:33,990 --> 04:00:35,790
(Lee Gwan Hee, Kwak Beom, Shin Seung Yong)

5341
04:00:37,060 --> 04:00:39,690
My head was spinning.

5342
04:00:47,070 --> 04:00:48,940
There is one additional announcement.

5343
04:00:50,900 --> 04:00:53,440
Last night, Pandora's Safe was opened,

5344
04:00:53,440 --> 04:00:57,040
and the price of an extra vote ticket
has increased by 10,000 dollars.

5345
04:00:57,040 --> 04:00:58,610
(Price increase in extra vote tickets)

5346
04:00:58,610 --> 04:01:01,620
An extra vote ticket
now costs 30,000 dollars...

5347
04:01:01,620 --> 04:01:04,680
and can only be traded in the Voting Room
during voting time.

5348
04:01:05,250 --> 04:01:08,460
Also, fund transfers
between players are allowed,

5349
04:01:08,660 --> 04:01:12,030
but they must take place in
the Voting Room with the butler present.

5350
04:01:12,490 --> 04:01:15,330
Voting will begin now.

5351
04:01:15,400 --> 04:01:17,930
Voting will close in one hour.
